title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Add Potato Buds to milk and water mixture.
Melt shortening and add to milk mixture.
Put in some of the flour; stir and add sugar, salt, yeast and egg, then the remaining flour.
Let rise once and knead down.
Make into rolls by rolling out dough.
Brush with melted margarine and cinnamon.
Cut and place in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Place thinly sliced apples in pie crust.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over the apples.
Mix remaining sugar with flour and margarine.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: savory thyme and pepper beef tips
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine seasonings; press evenly onto roast.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer so bulb is centered in thickest part.
Do not add water or cover.
Roast approximately 25 to 35 minutes per pound for medium rare to medium doneness.
Remove roast when meat thermometer registers 140° for medium rare or 155° for medium. Let stand 15 minutes.
Carve roast into thin slices.
(Takes about 3 hours.)

title: beef bar-b-q
directions: Cook beef stew	meat
until
tender,
very tender, in 3 cups water.
Pour broth	from pan and make sure you still have 3 cups of broth.
Chill
meat; then pull apart with fork.	Put 2 1/2 cups broth back	in pan.
Add next 8 ingredients and the meat.
Mix thoroughly and
simmer
for
1/2 hours.	Add 1/2 cups broth and a little flour to thicken.	Add to meat mixture and simmer a few minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; peel while hot and set aside to keep warm.
Saute celery and onions
until
tender
in 1/4 cup reserved bacon drippings.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix butter, catsup, chili powder, brown sugar, salt and red pepper in small pan.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Place in pan and brush with sauce. Bake for 30 minutes, brushing occasionally with sauce, until potatoes are tender.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain, crumble and set aside.
Grate potatoes and drain excess liquid.
Add all ingredients to potatoes and mix well.

title: cheese-olive puffs
directions: Grate cheese.
Using
blender,	mix
cheese,
flour and paprika.
Add margarine;
mix
well.
Chill.
For
each
puff, use a generous teaspoon and shape into a ball.	Push finger in center to make a deep depression; insert olive and shape dough around to fully cover olive (3 to 4 dozen small olives).
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, or until baked but not browned. Serve hot. Puffs can be frozen raw.
Thaw and bake as needed.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Brown seasoning in cooking oil.
Add crawfish, cream of mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted. Pour mixture in pie shell; cover with other pie shell.
Pinch edges and cut slits in center of shell.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yum Yum!!

title: scalloped potatoes and cabbage
directions: Put 1/2 of the potatoes and cabbage in a baking dish. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the onions and dot with 2 tablespoons of the butter. Sprinkle on 1/2 cup of the cheese. Repeat with remaining potatoes, cabbage, onions, butter and cheese. Pour milk over top layer and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar.
Heat milk to scald.
Add margarine; cool to warm.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and yeast mixtures.
Mix; knead until soft dough is formed.
Place in greased bowl; grease top of dough.
Cover; place bowl in pan of warm water.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Turn dough out on floured board; divide in half.
Shape into rolls.
Place on greased pans. Cover; let rise in warm place for 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes, until done.
Makes 2 dozen dinner rolls.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix rice with dressing; chill for 3 hours.
Chop vegetables into small pieces.
Mix all together with rice; chill overnight.

title: potato rolls
directions: Bake the potatoes.
Peel and add butter, onion, eggs, parsley, cheese and seasonings.
Shape into small (2 or 3-inches) rolls. Roll in cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 25 to 30 rolls.
Serve while
hot.

title: playful dough cookies
directions: Beat butter until softened.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Beat in vanilla.
Gradually add flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Divide mixture into several parts.
Add food coloring to each part, kneading with your hands until smooth. Form the dough into shapes about 3/4-inch thick.
Place cookies about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until firm, not brown.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 2 cups of dough.

title: herbed bread sticks
directions: Mix together and brush on hot dog buns which have been cut into strips.
Bake at 200° for 3 hours or at 300° for 45 minutes. You can use up stale buns this way.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, sugar and oil. Mix well.
Add vanilla, zucchini and frosting into dry mixture. Beat well.
Bake in a Bundt pan or large loaf pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: cool tomato consomme
directions: Bring to boil in a saucepan (non-reactive), tomato juice, sugar, garlic cloves and basil.
Simmer mixture stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Strain the mixture through sieve into bowl.
Stir in chicken broth, white wine, salt and pepper.
Chill. Divide into bowls and garnish with a slice of lemon or lime. Serves 6.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk and crumbs, together.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with milk and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: santa fe dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Heat on medium setting for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with dip chips.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake until done (approximately 30 minutes) at 350°.

title: barbara whalen's chicken supreme
directions: Pam a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread rice in bottom of dish and add water.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Cover with onion soup, mushroom soup and parsley and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: moma's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together in bowl.
Mix well.
Put in baking pan and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain grease off.
Top with ketchup and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: honey rice muffins
directions: Beat butter and honey together.
Add eggs and rice.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peppery london broil
directions: With a meat fork, poke holes in both sides of meat.
Make a paste with garlic, seasoned salt and red pepper; rub over both sides of meat.
Place steak in a gallon size plastic bag.
Add Worcestershire sauce and close bag.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours, turning once.
Remove meat; discard marinade.
Broil or grill over hot coals until meat reaches desired doneness, 4 to 5 minutes each side.
To serve, slice thinly across the grain. Yield:
2 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute hamburg with spices in a small amount of olive oil. Cook until hamburg is done.
Drain in colander and put back into large skillet.
Add 1 can of cream of chicken soup to meat and 1/4 cup water.
Cook until heated through.
Add sour cream 15 minutes before serving.
Boil egg noodles and drain; add to meat mixture and stir well.
Serve with rolls, etc.

title: penny's punch concentrate
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a 1-gallon container. Mix as needed: 1 part punch to 3 parts water.

title: zenobia bryant's southern corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: simple seven cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and blend well.
Serve chilled on lettuce if desired.

title: gourmet chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups and sherry.
Place 1/3 of sauce on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add rice and seasonings (1/2 of package) over that, then 1/3 sauce.
Add chicken pieces and then add last 1/3 of sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and almonds.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes good 8 servings.

title: mudball cookies("let the kids make this one")
directions: Mix oats, nuts and cocoa mix together.
Add peanut butter and honey.
Mix everything in the bowl until it looks like mud.
Put graham cracker crumbs in another bowl.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Remove meat from bone and place meat on bottom of baking dish. Cover meat with potato slices.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Add the water, if needed, to completely cover all.
Bake at 350° until meat is tender.
Do not add salt.

title: carol's famous veggie quiche
directions: In a very
large
copper-bottom
frying pan, heat olive oil. Toss in
sliced
onions
and
chopped garlic.
We like a lot! Slice potatoes
and grate carrots and add.	According to taste, add chicken
bouillon,
Tabasco, curry, or whatever you want it to taste like.
Cook slowly until vegetables are soft, but not mush. A
little
more
than
"al	dente".
Put in pie crust.
Sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese over veggies.
Beat together eggs (1
per person),
"light"	cream cheese and add milk to cover mixture
in pie shell. Bake at 350° for about an hour.	Top is fluffy and golden brown.

title: white christmas crunchies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips until smooth.
Add peanut butter and stir constantly.
Stir in peanuts, raisins and cereal. Make sure ingredients are well coated.
Pour confectioners sugar in grocery bag.
Pour ingredients in grocery bag with sugar and shake well.
Store in tight jar.

title: christmas casserole
directions: Layer bread, meat, and cheese.	Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion and water. Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.	Cook in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour, uncovered.

title: pink ladyfinger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add extract.
Add flour and mix; add rolled oats.
Using 1 teaspoon, shape into oblong 2 1/2-inches long (finger shaped) cookies.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 325°.
After cooled, ice with:

title: sauteed soft crabs
directions: Pat cleaned soft crabs with paper to dry; salt and pepper each crab.
Lightly dust with flour.
Fold back shell on each side and sprinkle 1/8 teaspoon dry mustard on each side.
Heat butter in skillet (strips of bacon may be substituted for butter).
Brown crabs for about 5 minutes on each side.
Put a dash of Worcestershire on each crab.
Serve on toast (with bacon strip or sprinkle with sliced almonds which have been sauteed in butter).

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Melt the cream cheese; stir while melting.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm in a chafing dish as dip.

title: arroz el pan con camarones(a spanish dish - rice in pastry)
directions: To Bake Shells:
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place frozen shells on baking sheet.
Bake until crisp, golden brown and puffed.
Remove top and soft pastry underneath.
Reserve top for garnish.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5 inch loaf pans.

title: amish bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Mix the salt in.
Cover and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain very well.
Make mixture of remaining ingredients and place over the cukes.
Set your pot on low heat.
Heat to a scalding point.
Do not boil.
Can and seal.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine the potatoes, onion, egg, flour, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix well.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Spoon 1/4 cup potato mixture into skillet for each pancake.
Flatten with spatula.
Cook over moderate heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Mix bread cubes with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Add noodle and mushroom soups.
Add eggs and chicken. Pour into casserole dish.

title: chicken ala king(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart casserole, melt butter on High in microwave for 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir in flour until smooth.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk and blend well.
Add large instant vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk. When well blended, mix into this mixture the largest size La Creme Cool Whip (or any kind large Cool Whip).
In large 9 x 13-inch pan, layer first vanilla wafers, bananas, 1/2 of pudding mix and repeat 1 more time.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put peanuts, sugar, Karo, water and oleo in skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until syrup strings like a hair and peanuts are cooked.
Add soda and stir well, then pour into a well-greased pan.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: fruit dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature. Mix marshmallow cream together with cream cheese. Mix well. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: spinach onion quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute spinach and onion; add salt and pepper.
In bowl put spinach and onion mixture.
Add cheese and mix.
In separate bowl beat eggs and milk.
Add to cheese and vegetables.

title: rocky road fudge bars
directions: Combine melted Candiquik with peanut butter and peanuts. Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom of waxed paper-lined 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour chocolate over marshmallows.
When firm, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: windows of the world's raspberry egg nog
directions: Puree raspberries in a blender; strain.
Beat egg yolks with 1/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat milk and Galliano liqueur (optional) into raspberry mix.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend dry ingredients into sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture in an 8-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in large pot of water until tender (about 10 minutes), covered.
Meanwhile, mix together in a bowl the chicken soup, carrots and sour cream.
Drain zucchini and onion and return to pot.
Add soup mixture and mix well.

title: german slaw
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in bowl; pour sugar over top.
Mix next 6 ingredients in saucepan, bring to a boil and pour over cabbage.
Store in refrigerator (will keep for months).

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Saute onions in melted oleo and mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dorothy's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together butter, macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add warm milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not stir or look at it for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for two minutes.
Make three layers and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ground chuck hamburgers
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in large bowl.
Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler and add to egg mixture.
Add flour, a little at a time, while mixing.
Then add vanilla.

title: deviled mushrooms
directions: Brown butter over high heat.
Add mushrooms and heat through. Add wine and remove from burner.
Let mushrooms steep, stirring infrequently.
Serve hot.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with as much mayonnaise as desired.

title: christmas toffee
directions: Put first 5 items in heavy pot on high heat.
Stir with wooden spoon until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Stir 5 to 7 minutes or until darker than brown sugar.
Stir in diced almonds.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Place Hershey bars on top of candy. Let melt.
Spread around and top with ground almonds.
Cool, chill and break into small pieces.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Butter bottom and side of pan.
Pour in fruit.
Pour cake mix over top of fruit (dry).
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: beans
directions: Put everything together in slow cooker on low heat evening before you need next day.
In morning stir up good and leave covered and resume cooking.

title: aunt nell's nut cookies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients well!
Add flour, soda and then nuts. Press firmly together, forming a roll 2 inches in diameter when rolled.
Wrap in wax paper; chill several hours.
Cut 1/8-inch thick; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mom's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion with chicken bouillon until tender. When squash is done add cheese; stir until melted.
Then add butter/margarine.
Let melt.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture in dish.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until stuffing browns.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: one pan pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in margarine in a large frying pan. Slice potatoes into thin slices.
Slightly drain pork chops and add vegetables in this order:
carrots, onion and then potato slices. Add chicken broth and spices.
Cover and simmer on medium heat for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for an additional 10 minutes.

title: hot cheese onion bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in onion soup. Add biscuit mix and stir until well blended.
Put into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread batter evenly.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake in oven at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: northwest salmon
directions: Place salmon on grill or on broiler pan. Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon and dill weed; smooth over salmon.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Combine meat of choice, vegetables, flour and cheeses.
Mix well and spread in unbaked pie shell.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour in shell.
Place on baking sheet and cook 35 to 40 minutes at 375°, until filling is set firmly.
Recipe can easily be doubled for 2 pie shells.

title: sausage
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until transparent.
Drain off fat.
Add soup, water and Minute rice. Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spicy rice and beans
directions: Heat the oil in a casserole or a large, deep saucepan.
Add the rice and cook until just turning opaque.
Add the onion, bell pepper, cumin and coriander.
Cook gently for a further 2 minutes. Add the Tabasco sauce, salt, stock and beans; bring to a boil.

title: zesty black-eyed peas
directions: Rinse and drain black-eyed peas.
Combine with celery, green pepper, tomato, garlic, mushrooms, pimento, salad dressing and 1 green onion (remainder to be used later).
Toss gently.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix ground apricots and coconut.
Add milk and blend well. Shape into small (1-inch) balls and roll in the confectioners sugar.
Let dry until firm.
Store in airtight container with extra confectioners sugar to coat.
Double batch will use 1 1/3 cups milk, which equals 1 (14 ounce) can.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix every ingredient except soup and water.
Form into small balls.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant rolls with mozzarella and ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut sixteen 1/4-inch thick rounds from center of eggplant. Arrange eggplant on paper towel-covered work surface. Sprinkle eggplant with salt on both sides; let stand 20 minutes. Pat dry. Arrange eggplant on large baking sheet. Brush both sides of eggplant rounds with 2 tablespoons oil. Bake until softened, about 8 minutes. Cool. Maintain oven temperature.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and corn chowder
directions: Place the chicken in a large pot with the water, salt, pepper, celery, sprig of parsley and bay leaf. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken from pot. Discard the skin and bones. Chop the meat into desired-size pieces but not too small. Strain the broth and return to the pot. Add the potatoes and cook, covered, until tender, about 30 minutes. Add the corn and cook until tender and hot, about 5 minutes. Add the eggs and taste for seasoning. Stir in the cream and heat just until ready to boil. Stir in the parsley and serve.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix in blender; store in your refrigerator.

title: curried vienna tarts
directions: Roll out pastry and fit into six 4-inch tart pans.
Set in large shallow pan for easy handling.
Bake in a 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Lower heat to 350°.
To beaten eggs add milk, curry powder, salt and onion.
Beat well.
Add corn and spoon into pastry shells.
Add sausages.
Bake 20 minutes or until custard sets.
Makes six 4-inch tarts.

title: raspberry jell-o salad
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13 dish.
Let gel for 1/2 hour.

title: restaurant lasagna
directions: Quick delicious lasagna.
Follow directions on lasagna box. Add already cooked wavy noodles to frying pan with other ingredients, after rinsing.
Season mixture to taste with garlic powder and oregano, while mixture simmers.
Once box noodles have softened, turn mixture into baking dish, Corning Ware or similar. Shred Mozzarella into mixture; stir, then add Ricotta cheese sparingly.
Oven setting should be on 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes without cover.
Bon Appetit.

title: buffet style beans
directions: Melt butter, then stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add sour cream gradually, stirring.
Fold in green beans. Heat and pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle with Swiss cheese, grated.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs mixed with melted butter. Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes until cheese starts to bubble.

title: fried okra
directions: Beat eggs and mix with okra.
Add enough corn meal to coat well.
Fry in hot oil until browned; drain on paper towel.

title: fattigmand(a norwegian pastry)
directions: In a bowl, mix together eggs, sugar and salt.
Add flour to make a stiff dough. Roll out onto floured board until quite thin. Cut in diamond shapes, one line at a time, and fry in hot lard, turning when slightly browned.
Remove and sprinkle with sugar. Store when cool in a tight container in a cool, dry place.

title: pork chop dijon
directions: Trim fat from chops.
In a small bowl, stir together salad dressing, mustard and pepper. Brush both sides of chops with mustard mixture.
Slice onion.
Spray a cold 12-inch skillet with nonstick spray.
Cook chops with onion in skillet, covered, over medium-low heat for 20 minutes. Turn chops. Cook, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes more or until meat is tender.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Make 9-inch pastry shell and let cool completely.
Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of pastry shell.
Put 1 pint of strawberries in shell.
Mash the other pint of strawberries very well and add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool mixture and then pour over berries in pie.
Chill thoroughly and just prior to serving, garnish with whipped cream.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use for fruit such as strawberries, grapes, cantaloupe, etc.

title: jenna's lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Chill until partially set.
Add cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and low-calorie whipped topping. Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Serve on lettuce. Makes 9 servings.

title: seven layer salmon salad
directions: *If using fresh green beans, cook about 2 cups.

title: meat patties with mushroom gravy
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, garlic, carrots and bread.
Mix well and form into patties.
Brown both sides of patties.
Pour the soup and water mixture over the patties.
Bring to a boil, then let simmer for half an hour or so.
Serve the patties with zucchini and corn Niblets.

title: fruit salad cocktail
directions: In a bowl, combine the fruit and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with pudding mix.
Stir gently for 1 minute or until mixture is thickened.
Fold in bananas.
Refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together. Place in greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Bake pork chops on top if desired.

title: quick 'n easy classic lasagne
directions: In large pan, brown beef.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer 15 minutes.
Cook lasagne as directed; drain.
Then put together as listed.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon swirl
directions: Mix hot roll mix as directed.
Let double its size.
Mix cinnamon, sugars and nuts together in bowl; melt butter.
Line a 12-inch pizza pan with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Knead dough.
Pinch off small piece and roll in hands to oblong 3/4 inch piece.
Roll piece in butter and then in sugars.
Start in center of pan. Continue round and round.
Let double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make glaze and drip over cinnamon swirl.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips well and pour into a lightly greased large casserole.
Sprinkle the potato chips on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Serves about 20.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: Combine sugar and lemon juice in a small bowl.
Beat with a wire whisk until sugar dissolves.
Add oil, one tablespoon at a time, beating until dressing is thick and creamy.
Cover and chill.
Combine spinach and strawberries in a bowl; add dressing and toss.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix and set aside carrots, crushed pineapple and walnuts. Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour large pan 13 x 9 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate bon bons
directions: Mix together milk, coconut, butter and pecans and add to powdered sugar. Mix well and chill overnight. Make into balls. Mix chips and paraffin in double boiler and melt. Dip balls. Put on wax paper.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix butter and flour.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Fold in cereal and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet and press down with a fork.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: kraut relish
directions: Blend kraut as it comes from can with other ingredients.
Stir well; place in glass dish.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator. Serve as relish or salad.

title: rose cake(1990)
directions: Cream together the Crisco, sugar, water and milk for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Beat whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Tint 1/4 batter red.
In 2 (9-inch) or 1 (9 x 13-inch) greased and floured pan, layer white, red and white.
Cut through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Ice and decorate as desired.

title: mexican casserole(easy and delicious!)
directions: Brown hamburger. Add water and taco mix.
Cook for 5 minutes. Add chili beans to meat mixture and stir.

title: tourlou(baked summer vegetables)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350°.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans according to directions on package. Combine ham bone, onion, celery, garlic and water to drained beans.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer for about 2 hours more.

title: great depression cake
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.
Diced candied fruit may be added.

title: apricotlets(candy)
directions: Cook apricots and water; mash and cool.
Measure 1 1/4 cups. Soak gelatin in cooled apricots.
Add sugar and heat in double boiler.
After heating thoroughly, transfer pan with apricots to a low flame and bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla; cool.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan lined with Saran Wrap and coat with white Karo syrup.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 days.
Cut into cubes. Roll in cornstarch, then powdered sugar.
May use applesauce in place of apricots.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Save 1/3 cup of water you cooked the broccoli in and mix rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wild rice chicken salad
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions.
Drain artichoke heart quarters, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir together rice, artichokes, chicken, and next 4 ingredients.
Stir together reserved 1/2 cup artichoke heart liquid, mayonnaise, and curry powder; toss with rice and chicken mixture. Cover and chill mixture 8 hours.
Serve on leaf lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and bake. Crumble half the cake in punch bowl and cover with pudding. Slice 2 bananas and add to bowl, then half the pineapple, half the cherries and half of the Cool Whip. Start all over again and garnish with nuts.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grease large flat casserole.
Arrange in layers:
tortillas, chicken, chilies, sauce and cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Top with cheese and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook 3 hours on simmer.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Mix in eggs (slightly beaten). Add vanilla; sift in flour.
Add melted chocolate and chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes in an 8-inch square pan lined with wax paper.
Do not overcook.
Cool in pan.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine peanuts, sugar and water.
Place over medium heat.
Cook and stir until mixture crystallizes and coats peanuts, about 10 minutes.
Spread peanuts in buttered 15 x 13 x 1-inch baking pan; sprinkle with salt.
Bake in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Lift and turn peanuts with metal spatula. Continue baking 15 minutes more and cool.
Store in covered container.
Makes 4 cups.

title: coke roast
directions: Score roast in several places.
Fill each slit with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Sear roast on all sides in oil.
Remove and blot fat from roast.
Place in foil lined pan.
Pour Coke and chili sauce over roast, then shake Worcestershire and Tabasco sauce over roast.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
This roast has a barbecue flavor and is excellent the next day also.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Veggies can be substituted for any kind you desire.

title: "corn bread what's good"
directions: Bake in 400° oven until brown, which will be about 15 minutes. Bake in a well-greased pan of your choice.

title: dump cake
directions: In a dry pan, layer ingredients in order given.
Do not mix. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: salsa(fresh chili sauce)
directions: Peel and chop the tomato and onion very fine.
Combine them with the chilies, garlic and salt in a medium-sized bowl.
Mix well.
Can also use a blender.
Let stand 15 minutes to develop flavor.
Will keep in a tightly covered jar in refrigerator 1 week or 4 months in freezer.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook and stir butter, mushrooms, onion and green pepper for 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Blend in salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk, water, 1/4 cup reserved mushroom liquid and instant bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and pimiento; heat through.

title: brown sugar drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk or water.
Combine dry ingredients together; blend into sugar mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Spoon dough onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly.
Frost when cool. Yields six dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Layer:
In a large bowl, tear lettuce up.
Slice onion really thin, crumble bacon and break into small pieces cauliflower or broccoli.
Sprinkle over top sugar, cheese and mayonnaise.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: cake pan baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in finger strips; add salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle cheese and onion soup mix, etc.
Cover with foil in an 8 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 24 hours.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Pare apples
and cut into chunks; then place in a bowl. Combine 1/2
cup
sugar,
tablespoons flour and the nutmeg. Pour over
apples and stir to coat well.
Spoon into pie shell and drizzle
with
lemon
juice.
Combine remaining sugar and flour in	a
bowl
and
cut
in butter.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and
slide	the
pie into a heavy brown paper bag. Fold end over twice and fasten with a paper clip or staples.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season chops lightly with Nature's Seasons.

title: homemade salami
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix each day for 3 days.
Keep refrigerated and covered.
On the 4th day form into 5 rolls.

(Put mixture on counter and roll to form sticks.) When rolls have been formed, put on top of broiler pan so grease will drop into pan. Bake at 140° for 8 hours and turn every 2 hours (very important!).

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix together the cake mix, butter and egg.
Press this mixture into the pan.
In a separate dish, beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Pour on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After cooling, cut and dust squares with powdered sugar.

title: baby wipes
directions: Cut paper towel in half with a knife.
Place half of paper towel in a Signature 3 or Modular Mate 3 Tupperware container or a large round container with cover.
In bowl, gently stir water, shampoo and baby oil.
Pour mixture over the towel; let soak in. The cardboard center of the towel will become soggy.
Pull it out and it will start the wipes.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Combine with onions in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over vegetables, tossing gently.
Chill several hours.

title: tostados
directions: Cook the black refried beans and the ground beef together until meat is fully cooked.
Spread the mixture on a tortilla. Cut the tomatoes into ropes and add them to the shredded lettuce; add the salt and lemon and mix the salad.
Add about three tablespoons of the salad to the tortilla.
Serve.

title: starr's christmas party punch
directions: Combine in a punch bowl.
Float a pretty ice ring in center. Serve.

title: oil dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients
well until all are blended together.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Allow to stand in refrigerator in covered container until flavors mingle.

title: mayonnaise bread
directions: Mix with mixer.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tin and bake at 475° until brown.

title: smoked sausage and beans
directions: Slice sausage in thin slices.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add sausage, onion and pepper to oil and cook until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes, on medium heat.
Add drained peas, tomato sauce, water and salt and pepper.
Stir together.
Simmer, covered, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat well.
Sift together and mix next 5 ingredients.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Fill paper lined muffin tins 1/3 full of chocolate batter.
Top each one with a heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture.

title: rainbow bananas
directions: Slice bananas.
Children can do this with a butter knife.
Roll slices in several different colors of jello.
Place on plate to see all the rainbow colors.
Little bitty children can do this.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch cubes.
In a large saucepan, bring water to boiling.
Add potatoes and carrot.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in fish, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile in skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Cook onion in skillet until tender.
Crumble bacon.
Blend 1/2 cup of the milk with flour, then stir into fish mixture along with bacon, onion, thyme and remaining milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly; cook another 3 to 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, then soda, bananas and flour.
Add nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in loaf pan.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Add water required on envelope of dry soup mix.
Add the corned beef into chunks.
Bring to boil.
The corned beef will separate as it cooks.
Put into a casserole dish.
Top with biscuits and bake until they are done.
Bake at 350°.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: Put vegetables in crock-pot.
Place roast on top and add consomme.
Cover and turn pot onto low before you leave for work. Add a little bit of cornstarch into broth and gravy is ready.

title: boiled cabbage
directions: Remove bruised outer leaves; discard and wash under running water.
Cut in fourths; remove the stalk part and cut in small wedges or chunks.
Place in large pot or saucepan.
Fill about 1/3 up on cabbage with water.
Cook on medium-high until tender.
It cooks in a short time (I test it with meat fork).
Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Also, add 1 tablespoon of sugar.
If more liquid than
you prefer, remove some before seasoning with two or three tablespoons of bacon drippings or margarine.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy (3 minutes).
Add flour and sugars until blended.
Beat in oleo.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 325° or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil together the vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cabbage, carrots and onion in a bowl.
When vinegar mixture cools, pour over cabbage mixture and mix well. Put into freezer container and freezer box for future use, or may be stored in refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.
Will remain crunchy until used up.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine first six ingredients with 1/2 cup grated cheese in a mixing bowl. Pour mixture in casserole dish and top with crab meat. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Just before serving, add ice ring or cubes.
Add ginger ale carefully.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Put all ingredients in order in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not mix. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Great with ice cream.

title: potatoes casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all ingredients except crumbs.
Put in buttered casserole and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4.
This recipe can be adjusted easily to feed more. Chunk hash browns may also be used.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Make a hole in center of mixture. Pour strawberries, oil and eggs in hole. Mix by hand until all ingredients are thoroughly combined. Stir in chopped nuts. pour into 2 greased and floured 9X5X3 pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-60 minutes.

title: plantation spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased or two 9-inch cake pans, well-greased. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash and stem berries.
Bring berries and lemon juice to a rolling boil and cook for three minutes.
Add sugar and bring back to boil and cook six minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars, let stand 24 hours before sealing. Makes about 2 pints.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour all juices in percolator.
Place sugar and spices in percolator basket. Perk and serve.

title: potatoes salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Peel off skin; cut in slices in cubes; add cut up onion, salad cubes (drain juice), carrot (grated), Duke's mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix all together and level it out on top.

title: crab quiche
directions: Line 9-inch quiche dish with pastry.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Combine eggs, mayo, flour and milk.
Mix through. Stir in crab meat, cheese and green onion.
Spoon mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheddar and bacon bagels
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bagels) in a bowl.
Spread ample amount on each bagel half and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients and use for fruit dip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased bowl.
Top with more Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes or until hot.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and let melt.
Put corn chips on plate and top with beef mixture.

title: mama's red devil's food cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order named and beat well.
Bake in moderate oven until pick is clean.

title: vanilla popsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into paper cups; fill half full.
Put popsicle stick in middle for handles.
Freeze in freezer for about 4 hours.
May add chocolate syrup for chocolate popsicles.

title: western lima beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add tomato sauce, brown sugar and cooked lima beans.
Put into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix together real well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pecan cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Heat and add eggs and oleo.
Stir until thick.
Remove from stove and add vanilla and pecans, chopped.
Put in baked crust and put meringue on top.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg yolks, Pet milk and milk together on medium heat until thick. Add butter and vanilla. Cook until it bubbles. Add cocoa. Mix well.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream and vegetable oil.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of batter in pan; save half. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half on top of batter. Pour rest of batter in pan and sprinkle remainder of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ground meat stroganoff
directions: Brown meat.
Add cooked shell noodles.
Add soup and milk to desired creaminess.
Add Mrs. Dash.
Heat.

title: tator tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Mix well with soup, Add beans.
Pour in a 9 x 13 inch pan, press firm.
Place tator tots on top, until completely covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Add water to equal the amount of juice (if needed).
Add to pudding mix; cook until thick.
Cool. Add all fruit and chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put in a 9-inch pie pan.
Cover with topping.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain green beans, corn and peas. Mix together all the ingredients and set aside.

title: colorado peach cobbler
directions: In bowl, combine sugar, flour, and nutmeg.
Add peaches; stir to coat.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2 inch baking pan. Spoon topping over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes or until filling is bubbly and topping is golden.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream if desired.
8-10 servings.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Place all ingredients in 4-quart freezer.
Can become banana ice cream by substituting 5 to 6 ripe bananas for the peaches. Decrease sugar when using bananas or other sweet fruits.

title: strawberry rhubarb cobbler
directions: Combine rhubarb, 2/3 cup sugar, tapioca and lemon juice in medium size saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer while stirring for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add strawberries and Kirsch.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix dough and gently spread over hot filling.
Bake at 350° until top is golden 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 1/2 hour and serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and celery.
Add mushrooms and remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: dad's date & nut cake
directions: Place dates in a bowl and sprinkle with nuts and baking soda. Pour boiling water over the dates and soda. Cover and let stand until cool. In another bowl, cream and beat together shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Add the cooled date mixture and add the flour and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes for layers (bake a little longer for a loaf cake).

title: jean's fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and if not moist enough, add more juice or applesauce.
Divide into 3 loaf pans sprayed with Baker's Joy. Cook in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: In blender, beat eggs, butter, sugar, flour, syrup, salt and vanilla extract.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over bottom of pie shell. Gently pour in syrup mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 40 minutes.
Yields one pie.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O together.
Stir in Cool Whip. Add oranges. Chill and serve.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add Karo syrup; mix well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternating with water.
Pour into a well greased and floured pan.
Bake in a preheated oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes or until center springs back when touched with fingertips.
Gingerbread can be served topped with Cool Whip or a white lemon sauce.

title: shrimp antipasto
directions: Place shrimp, cheese and olives in a large shallow dish.
In a 1 pint jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine remaining ingredients except salami and pepper.
Shake well.
Pour over shrimp mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Add salami and pepper.
Toss.
Drain. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: joy's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Blend in sugar, spice, salt and flour; mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; then reduce heat to 325° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 pies.

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a pastry pan.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in 425° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach dry. Stir together all ingredients. Serve with Hawaiian bread or crackers.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Bake pecans in a 300° oven for 25 minutes.
Beat 2 egg whites, salt and sugar.
Pour pecans in mixture and coat well.
Melt stick of butter on pan and pour pecans on pan.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
The last 10 minutes, sprinkle with cinnamon and stir.

title: 4 layered dessert
directions: Mix well and pat in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes; cool.

title: "punch bowl" bloody mary
directions: Mix all ingredients (except vodka) with juice.
Store in container overnight at least.
Pour over ice ring in punch bowl and add vodka. Excellent for brunch or holiday parties.
Ice ring can match the theme of party, i.e., holiday leaves, summer flowers.

title: lemon seasoned chicken breast
directions: In a small dish; combine all ingredients except chicken and parsley. Arrange chicken breast bone-side up on a microwave roasting rack, meatiest portions to outside of dish. Brush with half of seasoned mixture. Microwave

on high 5 minutes. Turn pieces over and brush with remaining mixture. Microwave 10 -15 minutes, or until meat near bone is no longer pink, rotating once during cooking. If desired, sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: baked cushaw
directions: Cut cushaw in 4-inch cubes and steam slowly in the 1/2 cup water until tender.
Pour off water, but save if mixture is too dry.
Mash cushaw and add butter, 3/4 cup sugar, salt and vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and spices together and sprinkle on top of cushaw.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For further browning, put under broiler for 2 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper together.
Drain grease off.
Add tomato sauce; cook until done.
In casserole put crescent rolls on the bottom, then hamburger meat.
Top with mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple pie coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in bowl, beating until smooth. Stir in pie filling.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, brown sugar and margarine in bowl, mixing until crumbly.
Add pecans, mixing well.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute
onions,	bell
pepper,
mushrooms
and celery in butter.
Add
olives,
pimentos, mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and hominy.
Put
in a 2 quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions; place in 14 x 10-inch pan, greased and floured.
While cake is baking, mix pudding and refrigerate.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip at medium speed on mixer.
Add instant pudding to cream cheese mixture and set aside.
Remove cake from oven and cool.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and let stand 1 hour.
In a large bowl, make stiff dough of the bread ingredients. Grease another large bowl and place batter in it. Turn dough over so oily side is up. Cover lightly with wax paper.
Let rise in a warm place. Punch down and place in 3 loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
You can make into rolls. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: party time cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add pineapple, pepper, onion, seasoned salt and 1 cup of nuts.
Form a ball out of mixture and roll in other cup of nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: italian pizza sauce
directions: Soften cheese and mix with sauce.
Bake at 350° 15 minutes. Use breadsticks to dip or spread on Italian bread.
If used on bread, bake together.

title: italian love cake
directions: Follow directions
on cake mix box and mix.
In a bowl, blend until
smooth, Ricotta cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar. Pour
cake mixture
into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cheese mixture on top of cake mix. Bake one hour at 350°.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out pizza dough thin; layer meats, onions, and cheeses. If desired, add pizza sauce to layers. Roll up dough and place in a pizza pan. In a small bowl, mix eggs, garlic salt, and Italian seasoning; brush top of dough with egg mixture. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: king crab pate
directions: Defrost; drain and cut up pieces of crab.
In a bowl, whip butter and lemon juice until fluffy.
Beat in mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, chopped eggs, horseradish and other seasonings.
Fold in crab, onion and parsley.
Cover and chill for several hours. Makes 3 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: cream cheese dainties
directions: Cream oleo, cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and stir into butter mixture until combined. Chill.
Shape into balls.
Roll in cereal and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: play dough
directions: Mix water, food coloring and salt.
Heat until bubbles form around edge.
Remove from heat and add oil and alum.
Add flour, all at once.
Mix and knead until smooth and spongy.
Store in jars or plastic bags.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: biscotti
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until well blended. Add melted butter, then add flavoring and lemon juice. Next, add 1/2 of flour (4 cups) and lemon rind and mix well. Mix baking powder with remaining flour and add to batter. Grease baking sheet. Divide dough into small loaves (about 1-inch thick and 2-inches wide). Bake for 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°. Remove from oven. Slice each loaf diagonally. Place on their sides on sheet and toast for 15 minutes.

title: danish apple pastry
directions: Blend flour, Crisco (cut as pie dough).
Put 2 egg yolks into a measuring cup and add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Pour milk and egg mixture over flour and Crisco to make dough.
Divide dough in half. Roll between wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Place 1/2 of dough in a jelly roll pan or a cookie sheet.
Layer cornflakes on bottom. Peel apples and slice.
Put apples on dough.
Mix 1 cup of sugar and cinnamon on top of the apples.
Place second half of dough on top.
Beat 2 egg whites until frothy and spread on top of dough. Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Make a glaze of powdered sugar and milk and drizzle on top of pastry.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or shallow ovenproof dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sliced green onions and chopped tomato, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: minted fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients except fruit.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Place fruit in large shallow dish.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Cover.
Chill for 3 hours or overnight.

title: lemon delight
directions: Step 1 - Crust:
Blend softened margarine with flour; add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Press into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until light brown.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Mix dressing mix, pepper, dill weed, garlic powder and oil. Pour over oyster crackers.
Bake at 200° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli-ham casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until browned.
Combine soup, milk, cheese and Worcestershire sauce in pan.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Mix together with rice and turn into a 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
(Take lid off for last 15 minutes.)

title: baked mochi cake
directions: Blend
together butter and sugar.
Beat together vanilla, coconut
milk and eggs.
Add egg mixture to sugar mixture. Add milk
and mix well, then add baking powder and mochiko and mix again.
Pour
into	well-greased
and floured 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place
on
rack
one level above center of oven. Bake
for
hour.
Completely cool before cutting, using a plastic knife.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine water and vegetables.
Cook until done.
Add soup (no water) and bouillon cubes.
Add Velveeta.
Stir until it melts.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice and peel apples and fill greased pie plate.
Toss with 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, combine sugar, margarine, flour and egg.
Pour mixture over apples in a pie plate.
Place in oven and cook for approximately 35 minutes at 350°.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: In a heavy pot, put oil and flour to make a roux.
When light brown, add onion and shrimp.
Fry slightly.
Add garlic and stir. Heat tomatoes; mash and add to mixture.
Cook slowly like a stew on low heat.
Add parsley.
Add a little hot water, about 1/4 cup to keep consistency of a stew.
Add corn and cook for about 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Season to taste.
Add about 1 1/2 cups of hot water and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Make stuffing as directed on package.
Spread half of stuffing over bottom of dish.
Cover with cubed chicken and mushrooms. Pour soup, diluted with milk, over top.
Add rest of stuffing mix. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy chicken cordon bleu for one
directions: Top chicken with cheese and ham.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
In small skillet, melt margarine and brown chicken. Add nutmeg and the soup mix that has been blended with the boiling water.
Simmer, covered, basting now and then for 20 minutes or until tender.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: cheezy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together well and put in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: verdura mista giambotta
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add 1 can tomatoes, zucchini, potatoes, celery and string beans.
Cook until tender. Season with oregano, salt and pepper.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and cut into bite-sized pieces. Cut up potatoes and boil in chicken broth until tender.
Mix all ingredients; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough of the chicken broth to moisten.
Spray a baking dish with Pam.
Place pie crust in baking dish.
Add chicken mixture and top with additional pie crust.
Spread top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nanette's serious punch
directions: Mix all of the above.
A designated driver is seriously advised..........

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, salt and peanut butter and mix well, gradually adding sugar and brown sugar.
Cream thoroughly after each addition.
Add milk and eggs, mixing well.
Sift flour and soda. Blend with first mixture.
Roll dough into balls about 3/4-inch diameter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beef goulash woodstock
directions: Heat shortening; add beef, cut into 1 1/2-inch square pieces. Brown quickly.
Add onions, paprika and a little flour; let simmer for 10 minutes on slow fire, then add salt, pepper and tomato juice and water to cover the meat.
Stir gently to blend the ingredients.
Let cook slowly until the meat gives under finger pressure.
Serve in casserole with quartered tomatoes and green pepper as garnish.

title: baked beans(good!)
directions: Brown meat and onion slightly.
Wash all juice off the beans. Mix meat, beans, onion with Kraft hot or onion barbecue sauce. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 hour.
Double recipe to use in large porcelain pan for church suppers.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan; reserve rest of batter.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, baking powder and salt; set aside 1/2 cup crumbs for top.
Add eggs and milk to remaining crumb mixture; stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with pie filling.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves a crowd.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar.
Cook mixture, stirring constantly. When cool, add lemon.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 450° oven, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken italian
directions: Place crumbs in shallow dish or pan.
Combine tomato sauce, garlic salt, basil and oregano.
Dip chicken pieces into tomato sauce mixture, then roll in crumbs.
Place chicken pieces, meaty side up, in shallow pan coated with cooking spray.
Do not crowd. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Do not cover pan or turn chicken while baking. Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add pumpkin.
Mix in flour, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and soda.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 large or 4 small loaves.

title: buttermilk-coconut pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Shield with aluminum foil after 25 minutes.

title: banana push-ups
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a blender and whirl until foamy, pour into paper cups and freeze. Push up from the bottom of the cup.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in vanilla, then eggs, one at a time.
Mix together.
Add flour; mix well.
Add buttermilk. Mix well.
Set aside.
Sprinkle pecans in pie shell; pour in filling.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before cutting.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add 1 1/4 cups shortening. Mix as for pie crust.
Add 2 beaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured pastry cloth as thinly as you can.
Use spatula to transfer to greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 6 minutes.

title: wanda's pound cake
directions: Grease a pound cake pan (loaf or tube pan) with shortening (to form a thin film with your clean fingers), then lightly flour it. Shake off excess flour.
Set the pan aside until cake mix is ready. Preheat the oven to 350°.

title: spinach feta bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add spinach, cheese, 2 tablespoons melba round crumbs, lemon juice and oregano leaves; stir to combine.
Spray 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray; spread spinach mixture in bottom of casserole.
In a small bowl, combine remaining melba round crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over spinach mixture and bake until crumbs are golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Serve garnished with lemon slices.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: calvin's bar-b-que drunken chicken
directions: Marinate over night as follows:
Wash each chicken thoroughly and pat dry inside and out.
Sprinkle chickens all over with seasoning including inside of cavity.
Place each chicken in a large zip-lock bag (one chicken to a bag) or, if cooking more than one chicken, place in a large container with a lid.
Pour salad dressing over chickens and refrigerate overnight.

title: honey french dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender until well blended. Serve over mixed greens or fruit.

title: reuben dip
directions: Cut corned beef into pieces and mix with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a casserole dish. Serve on Triscuits crackers.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch dish; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Layer ingredients in dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: a "lite" meat loaf
directions: Combine all.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in a loaf pan or baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
The last 10 minutes, pour 1/4 cup of sauce on top of meat loaf.

title: mushrooms santa fe
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, sour cream, onions, cilantro and chilies, set aside.
In small saucepan, combine butter and garlic.
Warm over low heat to melt butter.
Brush mushrooms with garlic butter. Fill each cap with 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until bubbly and golden, about 3 minutes.

title: margarita
directions: Moisten cocktail glass rim with fruit grind.
Spin rim in salt.
Shake ingredients with cracked ice.
Strain into glass.

title: lisa's vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until half done.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Combine Velveeta and soup.
Cook until Velveeta is melted.
Combine all ingredients in a baking dish and bake until heated through.
(Ham chunks can be added, but these are optional.)

title: grape punch
directions: In saucepan, combine grape juice, cinnamon, cloves and sugar. Simmer for 10 minutes; strain.
Stir in orange and lemon juices. Serve hot or cold.
Yields 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: sour cream from cottage cheese
directions: Blend cottage cheese until smooth and creamy.
Add lemon juice and salt to taste.
Goes well as a topping for baked potatoes or can be used with dry onion soup mix to make onion dip.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Cook rice.
Mix broccoli and rice together. Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, onion, sour cream and part of cheese to broccoli mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; top with cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Cut the chocolate into approximately 1/4-inch chunks. Combine the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Beat together the butter, sugar and vanilla. Beat in the egg.
Stir in the flour mixture. Add the oats, nuts and chocolate.
Drop the dough by level teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until the edges brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cookies cool 1 minute on baking sheets before removing to racks.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: egg snacks
directions: When eggs are cool, cut in half and scoop out the yolks.
Fill eggs with tuna or egg salad.

title: chili
directions: Saute hamburger, onions and green and red pepper in frying pan. Shake on the spices. Brown slightly and pour into large pot and add remaining ingredients. Simmer for approximately 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
Or with salad and sour cream.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep, rectangular baking dish.
Mix flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add milk; stir.
Pour mixture into melted margarine and spoon in cherries (with sugar added).
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat and add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Heat soup, butter, and cheese until cheese is melted. Stir constantly. Pour over broccoli and rice. Bake 45 minutes at 350.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix cereal, sugar, flour, salt and soda in a large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator.
Keeps well for up to six weeks. Bake as many as desired each time at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Blend one cup of love and one-half cup of kindness.
Add alternately in small portions one cup of appreciation and 3 cups of pleasant companionship into which has been sifted 3 teaspoons of deserving praise.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in electric skillet on both sides (10 to 15 minutes).
Salt and pepper. Place 1 slice of onion (medium thickness) and 1 slice of green pepper ring on each chop. Cover all with undiluted tomato soup. Simmer at 250° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oriental rice casserole
directions: Brown beef or cook chicken and mix with soy sauce.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Mix this with meat.
Stir in soup.
Add vegetables and rice.
Mix well.
Can mix this in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Take out of oven and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients except a small amount of cheese and crackers.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: baked rice pilaf
directions: Saute the garlic and rice in the butter or margarine until golden.
Pour into a casserole.
Add the broth and salt.
Cover tightly and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed.
Add the cheese and stir until cheese is well mixed and the rice is fluffy.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix in order, except for 2/3 cup chopped nuts.
Shape into ball or put in nice dish.
Roll or pat remaining nuts.
This can easily be made in a food processor.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Combine butter and cheeses.
Add sugar, sour cream, eggs and milk.
Combine noodles with mixture.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with frosted flakes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fast method potato salad
directions: Bake 6 large potatoes in microwave until done.
Peel and chop potatoes, adding two chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Chop onion and celery and add potatoes.
Blend in mayonnaise; mix well.
Stir in pickles and pickle juice.
If you like warm potato salad, mix together while potatoes are still warm and serve immediately or refrigerate if desired.

title: quick blackberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl at the same time; mix for 2 minutes.
Do not overmix.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° until done when tested.
Frost with caramel glaze.

title: skillet chicken paella
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
In 10-inch skillet, cook chicken strips, half at a time, in hot oil 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet; add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add broth, uncooked rice, oregano, paprika, salt, pepper and turmeric.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, pimento and frozen peas to skillet; cover and simmer 10 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Stir in cooked chicken; cook through, about 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: banana-oat tea loaf
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and cloves; add to creamed mixture alternately with mashed banana and milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in oats, raisins and pecans.
Spoon batter into 2 greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to oil.
Then add eggs, pumpkin, spices (sifted with flour), water and raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: challah
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large bowl; rest for a moment.
Add salt, sugar and shortening.
Blend in eggs and 1/2 flour (save a small amount of the egg).
Slowly add rest of flour and stir until dough is stiff.
Turn on lightly floured board and knead until satiny-smooth.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double in size (about one hour).
Punch down.
Cut into equal portions and roll into strips.
Braid strips and seal ends.
Place on greased sheet.
Let rise one hour.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Put on greased pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook until they form a little ball in a cup of water. Add vanilla, butter and nuts. Beat by hand until mixture begins to harden.
Place on greased plate or shallow pan or bowl.
Eat and enjoy.

title: lentil pasta soup
directions: Combine 4 cups water and next 17 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining 2 cups water, orzo and vinegar.
Cover and simmer an additional 30 minutes, until lentils are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Contains 134 calories per 1 cup soup.
Servings:
4 gallons.

title: medley of vegetables
directions: Prepare peas, broccoli and corn according to package directions.
In saucepan, place prepared vegetables.
Stir in almonds and pimentos.
Put bouillon cube in hot water to dissolve. Add onion and dry mustard to the dissolved cube.
Mix.
Add to the vegetables.
Cook until heated through.

title: crunchy raisin oat cookies
directions: Mix well.
Flatten to 2-inches in diameter (the flatter, the crisper).
Sprinkle with sesame seed or poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: snowflakes(press cookies)
directions: Place half of the peanuts in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan. Set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter chips over low heat.
Add milk and marshmallows.
Cook and stir until melted.
Pour over peanuts.
Sprinkle the remaining peanuts on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Dice bacon - fry crisp - drain. Add peas with peanuts. Mix in other ingredients, stirring well. Refrigerate.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Slice English muffins in halves and then each half in quarters.
Arrange on a cookie sheet.
Mix the remaining ingredients well, using a hand mixer at medium speed.
Spread mixture on the quartered muffins.
Freeze at least 30 minutes if you plan to use in the evening.
(This recipe freezes very well and can be made up to 2 weeks ahead.)
To serve, place crab muffins on cookie sheet and broil until golden and puffy.
Yield 48.

title: frozen island dessert
directions: Prepare lemon pudding according to package directions using 1/2 cup sugar and 3 cups water. Remove pan from heat. Add butter and stir until completely mixed. Put shortcake cups in individual serving bowls. Put a large scoop of vanilla ice cream in the center of each shortcake cup. Pour warm lemon sauce over the ice cream to form an ocean around the frozen island. Quick, easy and delicious dessert.

title: meatballs wrapped in bacon
directions: Combine beef, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 balls.
Place 1 slice bacon around each meatball and fasten with toothpick.
Press meatballs and bacon together until firm.
Brown on all four sides in skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat to desired degree of doneness.

title: scalloped eggplant(from 1975 edition)
directions: Pare eggplant; cut in 1-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling water for 8 minutes and drain.
Add egg, milk, butter, onion and cracker crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Sift the flour before measuring.
Add salt and sugar to flour and sift again.
Mix shortening thoroughly with flour mixture. Beat egg.
Add water and vinegar and beat well.
Pour over flour mixture and blend.
(Will be more moist than standard pastry.) Wrap in waxed paper and chill at least 30 minutes.
Dough may be left in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.
Roll out on aluminum foil. Makes 2 double crusts.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in a covered container.
Put about 2 teaspoons or more to a cup of hot water.

title: custard fruit pie
directions: Sprinkle crust with flour and fill with fruit and dust fruit with sugar.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and milk.
Beat egg whites and add to yolk mixture.
Pour custard over fruit.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue baking until crust is golden brown.

title: our favorite meat loaf(microwave recipe)
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Set aside.

title: cappuccino smoothies
directions: In a blender, combine the yogurt, milk, (sugar, if desired) and chocolate syrup. Add ice cubes and 1/4 cup marshmallows. Cover and process until well blended. Pour into chilled glasses. Top with the remaining marshmallows. Yield: 3 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator to chill.
Will keep for several days.

title: toffee
directions: Lightly butter a cookie sheet and spread with pecans.
Heat sugar and butter over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 320° on candy thermometer.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Spread evenly.
Cool completely and break into small pieces.

title: the mexican dish
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Cook hamburger with onion; drain.
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix according to package directions. Layer baking dish in the following order: black beans, hamburger and onions, salsa, cheese, and cornbread mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: lapienie
directions: Cut bacon up small and fry crisp.
Drain off grease except for a tiny bit.
Add broccoli, cut up small, and add water and cook until broccoli is done.
Add potatoes.
Add barley and simmer all together, about 10 minutes or until all warmed and flavor is through.
Add salt and pepper to taste and lots of butter.

title: fruited chops
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Brown chops on both sides.
Stir in chicken broth, soy sauce and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: mom's chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 of the chicken.
Open soup, spread over chicken.
Place cheese on top of soup.
Put rest of chicken on cheese.
Put stuffing on the chicken.
Pour broth over stuffing.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: upside down cake
directions: Beat 1 minute.
Place in ungreased pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts on batter. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: You will need paper cupcake liners and a muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all the ingredients together in a bowl. Blend until smooth.
Place a paper cupcake liner in each muffin section.
Fill each liner half full with the cream cheese mixture. Bake in the oven for 15 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Top each cheese cake cookie with cherry pie filling.
Delicious.
Great at parties for kids.

title: no bake bars
directions: Melt butter, chips and sweetened milk in microwave. Mix well and let cool. Add the 1 bag of marshmallows. Butter a 9 x 13 pan. Put 1/2 of the peanuts in the bottom of the pan, then add marshmallow mix and top with rest of peanuts. Butter hands and press down. Refrigerate. Cut into bars when set.

title: garlic cheese
directions: Make into balls or log rolls; roll in chili powder.
Chill in refrigerator several hours.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Serve with your favorite party crackers.

title: "the best" bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350`.
Grease Bundt pan well.
Mix all ingredients very well in large bowl.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake 50 minutes to 1 hour until done or when toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.
Let cool very well before removing from pan.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top, if desired.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix rice, sugar, pineapple and vanilla.
Add marshmallows and cherries.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff; fold into rice mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy chicken mac bake
