directions: In 2-quart saucepan in hot margarine, cook onion until tender. Stir in soup, milk and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni, 1 cup of cheese and chicken.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Top with 3/4 cup cheese and bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and both sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately after removing cookies from the oven, press a miniature peanut butter cup into the center of each cookie until only the top of the peanut butter cup shows.
Let cool for 10 minutes, then remove from muffin tins. Store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 40 cookies.

title: overnight veggie salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over veggies.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Yields 10 to 12 servings.
Keeps good for several days.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until fork-tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients with broccoli.
Spread buttered bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Add apples, pecans, flour, soda, salt, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: meltaway cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla. Sift flour and salt; stir in.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet (cookies do not spread).
Bake for about 8 minutes until set, but not brown.
Watch.
While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
(I do not.) Makes 5 dozen cookies the size of a quarter.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Fry onion in fat or drippings until soft and light yellow. Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 15 minutes or until fairly thick.
Serve hot on roasted meats.
This sauce may be made up and kept in a covered jar.

title: e-z macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in casserole dish and place in oven.
After the butter melts, add the remaining ingredients in the order given.
Stir occasionally.
Bake one hour.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: In large mixing bowl (at least 3-quart), beat the eggs well. Add coffee, vanilla, chocolate syrup and whipping cream.
Mix well (use electric mixer on low).
Add half and half, condensed milk, whiskey and brandy.
Stir with large spoon.
Bottle and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 fifths.

title: bambi pie
directions: Mix sugar and melted margarine.
Mix flour, meal and sugar together, then add to eggs and other sugar mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onions in butter 10 minutes or until tender. Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes or more.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and cook gently 10 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and pour over vegetables, cheese, onion and bacon.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Mix all together.
Pack into small covered roaster.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: boston cream pie loaf
directions: Slice cakes into 2 layers.
Place bottom layer on plate and spread some pudding on it.
Put top layer on and drizzle ice cream topping on top.

title: artichoke pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on Boboli crust. Bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: snow drop cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add sugar and vanilla. Stir in nuts and morsels.
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet. Heat oven to 350° and turn oven off when you put cookies in. Leaves 3 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pans that are greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white beans
directions: Thoroughly wash beans.
Boil beans in water for 2 minutes. Meanwhile, fry the bacon until almost crisp.
Take the beans off the heat; drain and rinse with hot water.
Put the beans back in clean hot water on low heat.
Add bacon and grease to beans.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt or salt to taste and the chopped ham.
Cook on low heat for about 2 hours.

title: nutty snack mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour butter
evenly
over
mixture;
stir gently to cover. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Remove from
oven; cool.
Store
in
an
airtight	container. Yields 6 1/4 cups.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and next 5 things. Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water. Stir in.
Mixture should thicken. Stir in shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil; add onions and cook slowly until softened.
Add zucchini and tomatoes; cook gently until zucchini is soft.
Add tomato paste, olives and juice; turn into a greased 2 quart baking dish.
Mix cheese and crumbs; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: springtime vegetable slaw(low-fat)
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, broccoli, tomatoes, celery and cucumber in large salad bowl.

title: sausage and grits
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain and save liquid combining liquid and 1 cup water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and add grits.
Cook 5 minutes. Add cheese and beaten eggs with milk.
Add sausage.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 350 ° until bubbly hot.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out and cut into biscuits. Bake until golden brown at 425°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables and olives in large bowl.
For marinade, combine vinegar and remaining in jar.
Shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over vegetables.
Cover and marinate overnight, stirring occasionally.
Makes 13 cups.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Grease pans or platters first!
Boil oleo, sugar and milk to a boil (full rolling) in a 4-quart saucepan, stirring constantly! Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly!
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased pans or plates.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
6 pounds.
Time:
20 minutes.
Pig out!

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix as listed; let raise for 15 minutes.
Pat down on sheets. Use Crisco, not oil, to grease sheets.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine ingredients and serve with chips.

title: gran polly's garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix together all cheeses, add worcestershire and pepper, mix well, form into ball, roll in parsley or pecans, chill until firm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil potatoes for 20 minutes and then peel them.
Chop up onions in small pieces and fry them for 8 to 10 minutes using vegetable oil.
Cut all vegetables in small pieces and mix well, adding 3 tablespoons of vegetable oil.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spread remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion bread
directions: Saute the onions in the margarine and set aside. Stir flour and Parmesan cheese together well. Cut in the shortening as you would with biscuits.
Add milk, using the amount needed.
Spread into greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
This can be refrigerated for up to a day at this point. When ready to bake, sprinkle Swiss cheese and onions (with margarine) over dough. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into pie crust shell. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Top with grated Key lime rind for extra zing.

title: corn bread
directions: Set pan in a 450° oven to preheat.
Beat egg until light. Beat in buttermilk and soda.
Sift dry ingredients; add to liquid mixture.
Beat in butter.
Grease hot pan (muffin or 10-inch pie plate); fill almost full with mixture.
Bake for about 15 minutes. Remove from oven; brush top with soft butter.
Place under broiler for about 1 minute, or in very hot oven for 3 to 4 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a square baking dish at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with topping poured over each piece after cut.

title: blackberry oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water.
Set aside.
Cream butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add flour and cinnamon.
Add oats.
Fold in blackberries.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar after cools.

title: mexicali hot taco salad
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, cheese, olives and chips.

title: alexander salad(fr. george)
directions: Cut up onion, rubbing green onion pieces against side of the salad bowl with a spoon.
This squeezes out the flavor and not only gives a good flavor to the salad, but tends to make the eating of the onion more mild.
Chop up lettuce, slice radishes and cucumber. Season.
Add sour cream generously, just before serving.
Do not be concerned if there is wilting, it's better that way.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, cream butter; add eggs and vanilla.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt peanut butter and margarine in pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: barbecue sauce for shoulder
directions: Bake 3 hours at 300°.
Add sauce, then cook another 1 1/2 hours.

title: dijon apricot sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, five minutes.
Serve on chicken, duck or turkey. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put pineapple chunks and marshmallows on top of bananas.
Make jello according to directions on package; pour over fruit.
Put in refrigerator to jell.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat sugar, melted butter, eggs and milk together in a large bowl.
Drain pineapple chunks and add to sugar mixture.
Then add the bread cubes and toss gently.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake until brown, about 1 hour.
(Very good served with pork or ham.)

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and beat.
Add the pecans, cherries, pineapple and flavorings. Blend.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: oyster crax snax
directions: Pour 1 cup oil over crackers.
Mix dry ingredients together and sprinkle over crackers.
Stir several times; store in airtight container to keep fresh (or mix oil, dressing and spices together, pour over crackers and continue as above).

title: kraut salad
directions: Wash sauerkraut; drain thoroughly.
Chop pimento, green pepper, celery and onion.
Mix in a bowl the sugar, salad oil, vinegar and cold water; add sauerkraut and remaining ingredients. Mix well; let set a day or a night in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Parboil broccoli.
Combine all ingredients.
Grease baking dish.
Place all ingredients into baking dish and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour, bread crumbs and oil. Shape mixture into cones and roll in flour, then in bread crumbs. Fry in very hot oil until brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Also good with ham, pork, beef and lamb.
(Try it, you may like.)

title: peanut clusters
directions: In large pan heat sugar, butter and milk to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix together peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
If mixture thickens, add 1 or 2 tablespoons of milk.
Let stand until firm.

title: strawberry jello fruit salad
directions: Whip the jello when it starts to set. Add other ingredients, then add 1 cup Cool Whip.

title: kentucky style chicken
directions: Combine flour, tomato soup mix and salad dressing mix.
Mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken in cold water.
Coat with mixture, twice if you want crispy.
Bake for 1 hour until tender.
Brush with oil and water mixture several times during cooking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate cinnamon bars
directions: Mix first eight ingredients with electric mixer.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan (or smaller pan for thicker bars).
Beat remaining egg white slightly and spread over batter. Mix 1/3 cup sugar plus 2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Pour chocolate chips over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Melt chocolate in milk.
Add flour mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks.
Stir in remaining mixture and cook for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Fry beef; add onion and pepper. Saute a few minutes. Add beans and tomatoes, chili powder and half the cheese.
Let simmer about 5 minutes.

title: summer squash pickles
directions: Let first 4 ingredients stand 1 hour.
Drain water off squash but don't wash off salt.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil. Add vegetables; return to boil for 1 minute.
Pack in sterilized jars; cover with vinegar mixture and seal.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix in order.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Bake pie shell 8 minutes or according to package directions at 450°.
Lower oven to 350°.
Toss cheese with flour and bouillon. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: tropical delight
directions: Blend all ingredients at high speed in a blender and serve.

title: old-time sugar cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in boiling water, cream or milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Put a tablespoon of butter or margarine on top of liquid before baking.
Bake in a hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a pan, melt butter, peanut butter, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Melt together.
Do not boil!

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda. Combine butter, sugars and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat well until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture and then stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: company chicken
directions: Pick meat off chicken.
Place in bottom of buttered pan.
Pour soup over meat.
Put bread dressing over this.
Make gravy from broth and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and melted margarine.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar and gently stir in Cool Whip and spread on cool crust.
Dissolve jello in water and add strawberries.
Put in refrigerator until barely set, then pour over cream mixture.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together; add water a little at a time to make a batter of thick consistency.
Drop into hot oil (375°) and cook until brown. Serve hot.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook over medium heat until the sugar dissolves and sauces thicken.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Serve warm.

title: hearty coleslaw for two
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, cut bologna in thin strips. In medium bowl, stir mayonnaise and salt.
Add cabbage, pineapple and bologna and toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce topped with eggs. Makes 2 generous servings.

title: pecan pies(makes 2)
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add all other ingredients and blend. Turn mixture into pie shells and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken breasts.
Mix flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Brown chicken in butter in 10-inch skillet.
Remove chicken from skillet to serving platter and keep warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put coconut and cherries on top if desired.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse
beans;
soak
overnight	in
water.
Heat
bacon drippings in large frypan.	Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until
tender.
Remove
beans.
Add
water to soaking water to equal
2 1/2 quarts.
Pour in frypan.
Add beans, pork, garlic and bay leaf.
Simmer over low 3 to 4 hours or until beans are tender. Add
parsley,
salt
and
pepper to taste.
Cook rice separately according to package directions.
Serve beans over hot cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate for a couple of hours. Slice 1-inch thick and serve with salsa.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove from frypan.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Blend in tomatoes, tomato sauce, bouillon cubes and seasoning.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add cornstarch, blended with water.
Cook until thickened.
Arrange on hot serving dish over spaghetti.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Add these ingredients to above mixture.
Boil all 5 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean and cut tops off of green peppers.
Cook for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Cook ground meat and onion until browned. Drain grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender (15 minutes).
Stir in American cheese.
Stuff meat mixture into peppers and stand up in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat in bite-sized pieces.
In clean sandwich bags, combine flour, salt, paprika and sage.
Crush basil and thyme; add to flour.
Shake well to mix.
Put stew meat in flour mixture and shake until meat is covered.

title: minute rice
directions: Boil water and put in rice; let it cook about 5 minutes.
Put in the tomato sauce and 1/2 can V-8 juice; put in chopped garlic and onion and simmer.
While it simmers, put in already cooked ground beef.
Let simmer for about 5 minutes or until done.

title: smoked turkey gumbo
directions: Make
dark
roux
(see
below).
Add
onions
and
bell pepper.
When
onion is clear, add parsley and green onion and cook for a few minutes.
Add small amount of water and stir to make thick liquid.
Add garlic and celery seed.
Add remaining ingredients
and
cover with 2 to 4 inches of water (depending on desired thickness).
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook 2 to 4 hours.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine everything except dried onions.
Place in 3-quart covered casserole.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until heated.
Top with dried onions.
Microwave an additional 2 minutes longer.
Serves about 6.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: In a 10-inch skillet cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Add potatoes, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Beat together eggs, milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; stir in ham.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture begins to set on the bottom and around edges.
Using a large spoon or spatula, lift and fold partially cooked egg mixture so uncooked portion flows underneath.
Continue cooking over medium heat about 4 minutes or until eggs are cooked throughout but still glossy and moist.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and make the dressing.
Chop broccoli and onion; add the sunflower seeds and raisins.
Pour dressing over mixture and let sit in icebox for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and when tender, remove from bones.
Place chicken in an extra deep casserole (makes a lot!).
Add the chopped, hard-boiled eggs on top of the chicken.
Add the chicken and celery soups, mixed with the 2 cups of chicken broth.

title: sauteed shrimp
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and add shrimp, garlic and lemon zest. Cook several minutes or until shrimp just turns pink.
Add all other ingredients and toss together.
Remove from heat and serve immediately over rice.

title: chocolate-topped oatmeal bars
directions: Combine frosting mix,
oats,
butter
and
sugar;
stir until blended.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Milk may be added if a thinner consistency is desired.
Tastes better the second day.

title: cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour filling in one crust and cover with extra crust.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: egg nog bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower florets from stems.
Combine with lettuce. Dice onion.
Mix sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Fry or microwave bacon, crisp.
Crumble on top.
Toss all ingredients just before serving.

title: open crock dill pickles
directions: Spread dill on bottom of 1 gallon jar.
Fit in pickles and top with additional dill.
Add garlic, if desired.
Heat vinegar, salt and water until salt dissolves.
Pour mixture over pickles.
Let stand at room temperature overnight.
Then place jar in refrigerator.
Pickles are ready to eat!

title: london broil
directions: Score meat by making shallow cuts at 1-inch intervals diagonally across steak in a diamond pattern.
Repeat on 2nd side. Place meat in a plastic bag set into a shallow dish.

title: classical cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs on top.
Layer evenly with butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, chopped nuts and coconut. Drizzle with sweetened condensed milk on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until barely golden brown.
Serve topped with ice cream or marshmallow cream and hot fudge sauce.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices; do not cut all the way
through.
Blend
butter, parsley, oregano, dill weed and garlic.
Spread
mixture
on
both	sides of bread slices. Shape aluminum
foil
around loaf of bread. Twist ends;
leave top open. Sprinkle
top with cheese and parsley flakes.
Heat in 400° oven 10 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix thoroughly graham cracker
crumbs,	gelatin, melted margarine and 2 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Press	firmly	on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.	Mix in bowl
cream cheese with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Add miniature marshmallows; mix well.
In another bowl prepare Dream Whip and fold
into
chilled marshmallow mixture.
Spread all over crust.
Then
spread
cherry pie filling.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Soften sausage at room temperature.
Prepare crust as directed on package.
Roll out in long rectangle.
Pat raw sausage in a thin layer over surface.
Roll from long side to long side, jellyroll style.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
(May be sliced and baked before completely frozen.)
Slice thinly and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and pineapple. Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar over top. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and cheese waffles
directions: Blend mustard and mayonnaise in a cup. Spread over bread. Put ham and cheese on 6 slices of bread, top with remaining bread. Spread outside of bread with butter. Bake in preheated waffle iron for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: mr. bennie's hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs in 1 cup of water. Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Gradually add enough water until mixture is thick and can be cut with spoon without separating.
Cut with long side of mixing spoon and drop in hot oil (350°).
Cook until brown.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hardy's biscuits
directions: Add all dry ingredients; dissolve yeast in hot water and add buttermilk and oil.
Add milk mixture to flour.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Take out as much as you need of the mixture for a meal and bake at 450° or 475°.
This mixture will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: chris jenkins' chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together and add enough milk to make a paste.
Add egg yolks one at a time and add the rest of the milk slowly.
Cook over a low heat until thick.
Pour into your favorite pie crust and cover with meringue.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook. Saute onion until tender.
Add green peppers; cook 1 minute and add rice.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover pot; place in oven.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into finger size strips.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with water; soak 1 hour.
Drain and pat dry with absorbent towels.
Coat eggplant with cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: olgie's pancakes
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Beat in a separate bowl the eggs until thick and piled softly.
Beat into the dry ingredients until blended.
Add the milk and melted butter; now add to the mixture.
Mix well.
Consistency will be thin and crepe like.
Delicious!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown stew meat in butter. Put meat in crockpot with both soups and milk.
Cook approximately 4 1/2 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
Half ann hour before serving, add
sour cream. Boil noodles, drain.
Add to crockpot.

title: cherry jello
directions: Stir well to dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pie filling and extract.
Put in mold and refrigerate until good and firm.

title: tex-chicken
directions: Put the chicken breasts in Pam sprayed pan.
On the top sprinkle black pepper, garlic powder and a pinch of salt.
Cook until brown.
Flip.
Again put down a sprinkle of black pepper, garlic powder and a pinch of salt.
When the chicken is almost finished, spoon on the salsa so it covers the top of the chicken. Then cover the top with thin slices of jalapeno cheese and finish cooking.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add strawberries, then ice cream.
Stir until ice cream melts.
Put aside in refrigerator to chill until partially thick.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan with thin slices of angel food cake.
Cover with a layer of strawberry mixture.
Add another layer of angel food cake slices and top with the rest of mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and butter until creamy. In another bowl, measure flour, spices, raisins and nuts. Mix until well coated. To the creamed mixture, add the buttermilk and soda. Stir the soda into the buttermilk first. Stir well. Then add flour, nuts, raisins and jam. Mix well. Bake in 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour at 325° for 2 hours or until well done.

title: breakfast egg bake
directions: First butter 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Trim crust off bread and cube bread.
Place bread cubes in bottom of pan.
Blend eggs and milk and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over bread cubes. Cut bacon in small pieces; fry and drain.
Put the bacon or ham, if you prefer, on next.
Then sprinkle the cheese on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: mac and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix spaghetti sauce, cheese from macaroni and cheese and water in casserole dish; add noodles. Brown ground chuck, drain and add to rest of mixture.
Stir in 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle rest of Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tiger butter
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with aluminum foil so that the foil extends 2 inches beyond two opposite sides of the pan.
Lightly spray the bottom and sides of the pan with vegetable cooking spray.

title: noble pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugars, salt and spices.
Add eggs and butter; mix well.
(Can be done in blender.)
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes, until center is set when tested with silver knife. This recipe has no milk.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Split rolls. Spread margarine mixture on both cut sides.
Cut cheese slices and ham slices to fit rolls.
Place 1 piece cheese and 1 piece ham on each roll; replace tops.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
May make ahead and freeze until heating time.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients and bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour. Sprinkle grated cheese over top and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: chili cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss Bisquick with cheese. Stir together remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: hot supper salad
directions: Brown meat with garlic; drain.
Add picante sauce, lime juice, soy and ginger.
Cook and stir 5 minutes until sauce has thickened slightly.
Arrange shredded lettuce and spinach on 4 plates. Spoon hot meat mixture over green.
Garnish with tomato wedges and sprinkle peanuts, green onions and cilantro on top.
Serve immediately.
Serve with extra picante sauce and fried wonton chips.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from pepper.
In a large kettle, bring water to boil.
Cook peppers 5 minutes, remove and drain.
Cook rice according to package.
In a skillet, brown beef and onions, drain and add tomato sauce, herbs, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Stir in rice.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: ceviche
directions: Cut fish into bite size pieces and marinate in lemon juice at least 6 hours.
Mix together remaining ingredients except parsley. Drain off 1 cup lemon juice. Stir in remaining ingredients and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Before serving, stir in the chopped parsley.
Serve in stemmed glasses on a lettuce cup. Glass shows off the pretty colors.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade mustard
directions: Combine water, dry mustard and turmeric.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, 1/2 cup water, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Blend mustard mixture into vinegar mixture. Add oil.
Remove from heat.
Add herbs.

title: roast beef
directions: Brown roast on all sides, approximately 25 minutes.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/4 cup flour and 1/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour. Combine flour and water; add to liquid.
Cook and stir until thick.

title: bread-and-butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions; soak in saltwater for 1 hour. Make spiced vinegar and let it come to a boil.
Drain water off cucumbers and add vinegar to them.
Boil 3 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: coq au vin
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp; drain.
Add chicken to skillet.
Brown well; remove.
Put onions, mushrooms and garlic in skillet.
Add all ingredients except wine and parsley.
Cook on medium heat 3 to 4 hours, then add wine and parsley.

title: spinach rockefeller
directions: Cook spinach 5 minutes and drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients and pour into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and dot with butter.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Combine macaroni, seasonings and veggies.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Combine vinegar and egg; stir into butter and flour mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Let cool.
Blend cooked mixture with mayonnaise.
Toss with macaroni and veggies. Chill.

title: picante-con quesa dip
directions: Combine in pan over low heat. Heat until smooth. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in applesauce, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir together ther flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil a potato in skin until done.
Peel and mash well.
Add butter, salt and vanilla.
Add enough powdered sugar to form a stiff dough.
Divide in half or quarter and roll thin between two pieces of waxed paper.
Spread with peanut butter and roll like a jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator.

title: dip - vegetable
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: auntie's pickles
directions: Boil all ingredients for 7 to 8 minutes.
Pack in jars and refrigerate.

title: evie's flourless fruit cake
directions: Combine all
ingredients
except for a few cherries for decoration. Mix
with
hands.
Turn
into
greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cake is done when no milk
oozes
out
when
pressed with finger.
Decorate with reserved cherries.
Let
cool.
Turn out on foil and wrap snugly.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix all.
Marinate chicken pieces with bones in the refrigerator.
Grill and baste.

title: one pan western stir-fry chicken
directions: In a large frying pan, saute the chicken in oil until tender and white.
Add onion, water and rice, including the seasoning packet that comes in the box of rice.
Stir and cover.
Cook over medium heat for approximately 5 to 8 minutes or until the water has absorbed into the rice.
Add the chopped tomato.
Cover and continue to cook on low heat for 2 minutes.
Add the lettuce; stir.
Cover and cook for another 3 minutes.
Tastes great with soy sauce for an Oriental dish.
You can prepare ahead and refrigerate.
Inexpensive and tastes great!
Serves 4.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with about 5 slices butter or liquid butter.
Top with pie shell.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and onions in chicken broth.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Add macaroni and onions and the soup.
Top with cheese; place in oven.
Cook long enough for cheese to melt.

title: hot florentine dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese in a 2-quart casserole on High for 30 seconds. Add milk, onion, Worcestershire, garlic salt and pepper; cream together. Stir spinach and bacon into cream cheese mixture. Fold in sour cream and pecans. Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after every minute until dip is heated through. Garnish with chopped pecans and parsley. Serve with crackers and/or bread.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Saute onions; add drained spinach and all rest of ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: val's chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter, crescent rolls, croutons and chicken.
Heat slowly until warm.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan; mix in chicken.
Put strips of crescent roll dough on top.
Sprinkle crushed croutons over dough.
Melt butter and pour over croutons.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix egg into Ricotta cheese.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scrapple
directions: Cook pork in 2 cups water with salt, pepper, onions and garlic until well done.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Grind meat when cool. In medium saucepan (2 quart) bring 2 cups of reserved broth to a rolling boil.
Add corn meal which has been mixed with 1 cup of cold water.
Stir corn meal mixture into boiling broth, stirring continually until mixture is consistency of corn meal mush or cooked oatmeal.
Add ground pork and continue to cook over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent sticking. Put in 8 x 8-inch pan lined with foil.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice into 3/8-inch slices, fry in small amount of margarine or oil, turning to brown.
Serve hot as breakfast meat.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender; cool.
Lay slices of cheese over pie dough; follow with spinach, then onion.
Beat eggs, adding enough milk to make one cup.
Add seasonings and pour over ingredients in the pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 35 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Serve piping hot.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, peppers and parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate the potatoes. Add eggs, flour, sugar, milk and spices. Mix well together. Add flavoring.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: party crunch mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal, crackers and noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Set aside.
Whisk together almonds, oil, soy sauce, garlic powder and onion powder in small bowl. Quickly pour over cereal mixture. Stir to coat evenly. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes. Cool.
Makes 9 cups.

title: roasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt margarine in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread pecans evenly in pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate or almond bark in top of double boiler (or in microwave); remove from heat and stir until smooth. Cool 2 minutes; add pecans and stir until well coated.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.

title: quick mix
directions: Variation:
Substitute 4 1/4 cups whole wheat flour for equal amount of all-purpose flour, but increase baking powder to 5 tablespoons.

title: cheese mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pasta, meat, soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add pepper, seasoning and 2 cups of the Mozzarella cheese. Add Parmesan cheese and pepperoni.
Mix. Place in baking bowl. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Mix together in bowl all ingredients, except peanut butter and chocolate.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Spread with peanut butter while hot.
When cool, melt the chocolate and spread over peanut butter.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain grease.
Drain beans.
Cut cheese into cubes and mix with Ro-Tel in microwavable bowl.
Cook on Medium-high until cheese is melted, stirring often (maybe every 3 minutes).
Mix in the beans and sausage and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pour chopped pecans in bottom of greased and floured Bundt pan.
Combine white sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Take biscuits and cut biscuits in fourths.
Coat with sugar mixture. Drop evenly in pan.
Then combine oleo, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger hash brown quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press hash browns in greased pie plate; brush with butter.
Bake 10 minutes.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Combine milk, eggs and cornstarch.
Stir into meat.
Add cheese (cut into small chunks) and Worcestershire.
Pour into hash brown crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in jacket until tender.
Cool and grate on large side grater.
Heat butter in heated soup.
Blend sour cream, cheese and onion in soup.
Stir in potatoes.
Put in casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and dot here and there with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: polish sausage casserole(kielbasa)
directions: Cook flour and milk, stirring constantly until thickened. Layer alternately the potatoes, onion and cabbage in a casserole dish.
Add sauce, 1/3 after each 3 ingredients layered.
Cover with foil, plastic or glass.
Cook in oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or in microwave for 35 minutes on Medium-high.
If using microwave, only add 1 1/2 cups of milk to sauce to cut out any boilover.

title: fiesta corn bread
directions: Melt shortening in pan in oven to coat bottom evenly.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted shortening. Mix just until blended. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Insert with toothpick in center. Done when it comes out dry. Use 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: filled eggplant
directions: Cut off the stems and peel the eggplants in strips.
Soak in salt water for 1/2 hour.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Fry both sides in oil; remove.
Brown the hamburger, onions and peppers in a frying pan, then add the tomatoes and parsley.
Stir and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cut slits in the sides of the eggplants.
Fill with the hamburger mixture.
Place the stuffed eggplants in a baking pan with 1/4 cup water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid (all 3) water and sugar in a large container. Pour in punch bowl.
Put orange sherbet in Kool-Aid mixture.
Pour 7-Up or ginger ale directly over orange sherbet.
A favorite of smiling kids!

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased pans and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt chocolate with oleo over low heat in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in milk.
In small bowl, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle over filling.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until puffed and brown.
Filling will be soft, but will set while cooling.
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: brunch hash brown casserole
directions: Cook sausage or bacon completely.
Crumble and set aside.
In a large bowl combine the first 8 ingredients.
Add sausage or bacon. Place in a large baking dish approximately 10 x 12 inches.
Bake in center oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach glace pie
directions: Simmer 1 cup peaches with the water for 4 to 5 minutes. Combine sugar and cornstarch and add to cooked fruit.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice.
Cool slightly.
Put remaining fresh peaches in the baked pie shell. Pour glace over the fruit and cool.
Serve with whipped cream. Serves 6.

title: sirloin tip roast
directions: Use roasting pan with rack.
Place roast in heavy-duty foil, long enough to hold and seal securely.
Sprinkle soup mix over roast.
Spoon mushroom soup over roast.
Seal foil.
Bake at 350° approximately 2 1/2 hours.
May also be cooked overnight in crock-pot.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Put taco sauce, taco powder and 1 cup water into browned beef; cook on low for 10 minutes.
Toss together lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Add chips.
Pour hot beef over mixture and stir.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook chopped cabbage until tender; drain.
Pour into casserole dish; saute pepper, onion and pimento in margarine.
Add mushroom soup and Velveeta cheese; cook on low until cheese melts.
Add dill seed.
Pour over cabbage and top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until bubbly.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll the dough in balls the size of a walnut. Pat down a little bit with a water glass. Should be thin. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on a cookie sheet.

title: baked lima beans and peas
directions: Thaw vegetables for several hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Place in greased 4-quart shallow casserole with tight-fitting cover.
Stir in basil, salt and onions.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with water.
Place lettuce leaves (outer ones from head lettuce) over vegetables, cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: made ahead biscuits
directions: Mix and set aside first 2 ingredients.
Put flour, soda and sugar into bowl and cut vegetable shortening into mixture until granules have formed.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Dough will be very soft.
Store in tight container and refrigerate overnight.
To bake, take as much dough as you need.
Roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake biscuits at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown and done inside.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining dough.
Will keep up to 5 days.

title: southwest soup
directions: Saute onions; brown meat and drain. Add all the other ingredients. Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: fudge wonder pudding
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Stir in milk, margarine and vanilla.
Turn into 9-inch square pan.

title: impossible pie(coconut)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Put all ingredients in blender on high for 30 seconds.
Pour in pie plate and let set for five minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup angel coconut.
Bake until set 35 to 45 minutes in center of oven.
Let cool on rack and serve.
Good!
Serves 8 people.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into 4 patties, 1/2 inch thick. May barbecue or broil on lightly greased broiler pan, about 6 inches from heat for 3 to 4 minutes per side or until no longer pink in center.

title: chili vermicelli
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, heat oil.
Add onion; cook until onion is tender.
Add chili; cook until onion and chili are well blended and thoroughly heated.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Serve hot pasta topped with chili sauce; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: perfect no-weep meringue
directions: Cook water, cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar in measuring cup in microwave until custardy.
Cover.
Beat egg whites and remaining sugar until stiff.
Slowly add hot custard mixture to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat and onion (drain).
Boil pasta and rinse.
Mix cheeses and eggs together.
Mix meat and cheese mixtures together. Stuff shells with mixture.
If any meat mixture is left, put in spaghetti sauce before pouring over stuffed shells.
Use 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (uncovered).

title: frozen angel dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with 2 tablespoons of sugar and melted margarine.
Press mixture on bottom and sides of lightly buttered refrigerator tray; chill.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; combine with milk.
Stir in lemon rind and lemon juice until thick.
Stir in 1 cup of coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in rest of sugar.
Fold gently into lemon mixture.
Pour into tray.
Sprinkle top with remaining coconut.
Chill until firm.

title: shellie's turtle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in large glass bowl at medium speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Add eggs and mix at high speed until smooth.
Fill crust 1/3 full with mixture and lace with caramel topping.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Pour remaining on top, repeat with chips, pecans and caramel.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool completely, cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate, preferably overnight.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fresh strawberry sauce
directions: Combine berries, sugar and lemon juice in a medium saucepan. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in extract.
Allow to cool before using.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Cream well, add eggs slightly beaten.
Have dry ingredients sifted together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Then add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake in slow oven at 275° about 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops and stuffing
directions: Melt shortening in skillet. Add pork chops and brown on both sides.
Remove from the skillet. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and set aside. Saute celery and onion in butter until tender. Combine the bread cubes and remaining salt, sage, thyme, pepper, egg and water.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Form stuffing into pyramid in center of 4-quart casserole. Stand pork chops on large end against stuffing.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: white fudge
directions: Let oleo begin to melt in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Brush sides of pan with melted margarine.
Add milk and sugar.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, about 8 minutes, whisking constantly to dissolve sugar.
Cook over medium heat, whisking frequently to soft ball stage (236°), about 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add candy wafers, Marshmallow Creme, walnuts and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Quickly pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
When firm, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Total cooking time about 40 minutes.
Yields 115 pieces or 4 pounds.

title: betty's dump cake
directions: Spread pie filing in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Add layer of pineapple; sprinkle cake mix on pineapple.
Cut butter into thin slices and place on cake mix.
Sprinkle with coconut, then nuts. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 15 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar after cooling for 5 minutes, then roll again in powdered sugar after cooling completely.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook chicken in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and reserve broth.
Cool chicken, remove from bones and chop into bite size pieces.
Drain mushrooms and reserve liquid.
Mix mushroom liquid and chicken broth in a saucepan.
Add celery, onions and bell pepper and cook until tender.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Cook noodles according to package directions and add to chicken mixture.
Mix in remaining ingredients and place in a large casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour with salt alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Make a paste of food color and cocoa.
Add to batter and beat well.
Mix vinegar and soda and add to batter, mixing well. Makes three layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hazelnut french toast
directions: Dissolve Coffee-mate in hot water; set aside.
In medium bowl, beat eggs and vanilla.
Add Coffee-mate mixture to eggs, mix well. Place bread in egg mixture for 20 seconds.
In a nonstick skillet over medium-low heat, add bread and cook until brown on each side.
Serve with maple syrup.
Garnish with fresh fruit.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add, a little at a time, until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 375° until light brown.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except last 2, and spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour.

title: summer tomato pie
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll out dough for 9-inch pie plate.
Leave excess hanging over and refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fajitas
directions: Wrap flour tortillas in aluminum foil and place in 300° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
While tortillas are warming, saute chicken with onions and bell pepper until done.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with grated cheese, diced tomatoes, lettuce, sour cream and salsa.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and add sour cream and soup.
Add onions.
Add cooked potatoes.
Put in crock-pot on low.
Heat for at least 1 hour.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mix.
Form into tiny balls; place on cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add bread and stir. Add cheese and sausage and mix well.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple sparkler
directions: You will need 5 (6-inch) wooden skewers.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Crumble beef into 2-quart casserole.
Stir in onion, celery and garlic.
Cook in microwave, covered, on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until beef is no longer pink and vegetables are tender, stirring once; drain off fat.
Stir in beans, taco sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick spray. Line with tortillas to form a shell.
Spoon cottage cheese over tortillas.
Top with meat mixture.
Cook, covered with vented plastic wrap, on High for 6 to 7 minutes; give dish a half turn once.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook, covered, on High for 1 minute more or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and dry onion soup mix together until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Reserve 1 cup of broth and mix with 2 cans of cream of chicken soup.
Remove skin and bone from chicken.
Chop the chicken coarsely.
Mix chicken, sage, black pepper, Veg-All and chicken soup mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: deviled party mold
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Lightly oil a small gelatin mold or bowl.
Fill with mixture and chill for several hours just before serving; carefully remove meat mixture from mold and invert on serving plate.
"Frost" mold with sour cream.
Serve with tiny party rye bread or crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry tea(miscellaneous holiday drink)
directions: Cook red hots in 2 cups water.
Add stick cinnamon and cloves. Let cool.
Add cranberry juice, orange juice and lemonade.
Add lemon juice.
Add 2 1/2 cups water.
Store in refrigerator.
When ready to serve (use) heat one cup of mixture to every two cups water.

title: plum tomato soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine the fresh and canned tomatoes with their juice; bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Add the baking soda; cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Stir in the chicken broth, tomato paste, basil, sugar and leeks.
Reduce the heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape.
Put in a deep pan. Pour 2 or 3 cups water in pan.
Peel potatoes and lay around meat loaf.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake (3)
directions: Mix jello and boiling water, chill until jelly like.
Work sugar and vanilla into cream cheese. Whip evaporated milk with electric mixer till fluffy and firm.
Mix in cheese mixture and jello.
Pour into a 9 x 12 inch cake pan with graham cracker crust.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix some of the juice from Bing cherries with cream cheese until very soft (not runny). Add remaining ingredients. Mix by hand. Be sure to cut cherries and pineapple in halves before mixing. I always double this recipe. Put in molds, clear glass containers, etc. Cover with foil and freeze.

title: kay's creamy mashed potatoes
directions: You will need an electric hand mixer.

title: best ever cranberry mold salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: chicken, broccoli vegetable saute
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of margarine with chicken for 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Cool.
Thaw vegetables.
Cut Provolone cheese, pepperoni and roasted peppers into bite size pieces.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, condensed milk and melted butter. Add pecans and vanilla. Shape about 5 ounces small balls and refrigerate.

title: fish cake fritters
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg to water and beat until foamy.
Mix into dry ingredients, stirring only to moisten dry ingredients.
Add kamaboko and green onions.
Drop by teaspoonful in heated oil.
Fry 1 minute or until delicately brown.
Serve with meal or as pupu while hot.
Makes 18 to 24 kamaboko tempuras.

title: cherry caramel ring
directions: Place 1/4 cup butter in 8-inch round dish.
Microwave on High until melted.
Sprinkle sugar over butter and corn syrup.
Stir well with fork.
Place a drinking glass in center of dish. Sprinkle pecans and cherries around the glass over the butter and syrup.
Take refrigerated buttermilk rolls and arrange them over the mixture in dish, squeezing to fit them in.
Microwave at Medium for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on medium until done (6 to 8 hours).

title: hamburger-squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wash, peel and slice squash.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt 1 cup margarine; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture to dry mix and beat well; add 1/3 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until cake springs back when touched.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice
carrots about 1/4-inch thick.
Cook until tender (don't overcook), about 7 minutes.
Drain.
Cut up pepper and onion. Mix soups and sugar well, then add vinegar.
Mix well. Then add oil,
slowly, and mix this well.
Pour over carrots, pepper and onion.
Mix well and put in refrigerator for a day.

title: stuffed sea shells
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic salt until crumbly.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in Mozzarella, bread crumbs, oregano and egg. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook shells according to package directions and drain.
Stuff shells with meat mixture.
Spoon 1/4 of sauce over the bottom of 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch glass baking dish. Place shells in single layer.
Cover with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: southwestern vegetable soup
directions: Coat Dutch oven with Pam; place over medium heat until hot. Add onion, green chilies and garlic; cook until tender.
Add water, tomato juice, canned tomatoes, bouillon, cumin, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, hot sauce, corn and green beans.
Stir well; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 hour.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into prepared graham cracker shell.
Chill.

title: spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour boiling water over this and mix.
Pour into a hot, greased, 2-quart dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 500°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into 13 x 9-inch pan, pressing out perforations.
Bake as directed.
Let cool completely.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Mix together in order given.
Bake in 325° oven (convection) for 25 minutes for muffins and 1 hour for loaves of bread.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Melt butter and add egg mixture.
Add dates.
Cook and stir until mixture is thick and dates begin to melt.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Cool slightly and roll in small balls.
Roll balls in 10x sugar or coconut.
Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: french meat pie
directions: Cook ground pork, onions and garlic for 3 hours on a very low fire.
When it begins to stick, add a little water.
As it cooks, mash the crackers in a little at a time to absorb
the grease. Add salt and pepper to taste.
When cool, put into a double shell pie crust.
Bake at 375° until browned, 30 minutes or so.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first three ingredients well.
Add potato chips and stir in flour.
Form small balls.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Press balls flat with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes.

title: easy "no fail" macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in well salted water according to package instructions. Drain. Spray casserole(s) with cooking spray. Layer half of macaroni in bottom of dish. Top with half of cheese. Repeat. Mix beaten eggs with milk and pour over macaroni and cheese mixture. Cooking time and temperature may be varied. Cook 1 large at 425° for about 45 minutes if you like it "set" and browned. Slower oven will result in softer, cheesier mix. Anywhere from 350° to 450° and 30 minutes to 60 minutes works; you can't hurt this dish. Men and women love it. It's good!

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Let cool slightly. Peel.

title: nut cups
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter; blend together.
Add 1 cup flour; mix together into large ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen (1-inch) balls and place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Press dough against bottom and sides.

title: crusty potato casserole
directions: Peel the
potatoes
and shred (you should have 8 cups). Add enough
water to cover potatoes, preventing discoloration until all
are
shredded.
Drain potatoes, saving 1 cup of the water. Heat
the
water, 2 tablespoons of the butter and milk to just under
boiling.
Pour
over
potatoes and stir in the onion, salt, pepper and eggs.

title: french cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add cake mix (dry), 1/3 at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
(If mixer is used, add last 1/3 of mix by hand).
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop by level teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool before removing from baking sheet.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl with undrained pineapple and mix lightly with spoon.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: Mix in blender and freeze in plastic pitcher overnight.
Add a package of frozen strawberries for a strawberry daiquiri.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Add flour one cup at a time. Add baking soda and vanilla. Chill for at least 1 hour. Divide into thirds and place on floured board. Roll and cut. Bake at 250° until done.

title: okra and fresh tomatoes
directions: Prepare okra and tomatoes.
Saute onion and green pepper in fat, stirring often, until onion is browned.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, over medium heat for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook another 5 minutes.

title: galaxy special
directions: Mix together and spoon into baking dish.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold on crackers.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Sprinkle chopped pecans evenly in the bottom of a well greased 10 inch bundt pan and set aside. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Cut biscuits into quarters. Roll each piece in the sugar mixture and layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and margarine and pour over biscuits. Bake for 30 minutes. Invert onto serving dish.

title: barbecued swordfish
directions: Sprinkle swordfish steaks with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil slowly for 15 minutes.
Place steaks on grill.
Baste with sauce.
Turn once and baste again. Cook until done.
Serve with more of the hot sauce.

title: sherry's lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts with fork.
Press into bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip and spread over warm crust.
Prepare pudding and spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip in container.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cajun lima beans
directions: Make roux with oil and flour.
Add onions and tomatoes. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add lima beans and add cold water to cover beans.
Cover and boil gently until beans are tender 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: caramel surprise
directions: Spoon alternate layers of ice cream and crushed candy into 6 parfait glasses. Top each with 1 tablespoon Kahlua.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients as given.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 7 minutes.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Place piece of foil 30 x 18-inches in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Place beef in pan.
Mix soup and onion soup mix; spread over meat.
Add vegetables; sprinkle with water. Fold foil over and seal.
Bake 4 hours in 300° oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick ponche de creme
directions: Beat eggs; add both sets of milk to even consistency.
Blend in rum.
Add Bitters to taste.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: baked rolled sole
directions: Beginning with short end, roll up sole, skinned side in. Arrange them seam side down in a well buttered baking dish just large enough to hold them in one layer and sprinkle them with the lemon juice.
In a small bowl, beat the eggs with the cream; add the cayenne, salt and herbs.
Pour the custard over the sole and put the dish, covered with foil, in a preheated 350° oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until sole flakes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in top of double boiler over simmering water. Beat three eggs until thick. Beat in flour, sugar, and vanilla. Cool chocolate mixture, beat in and add nuts. Grease and flour an 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes till tended and dice with fork.
Combine other ingredients while potatoes are boiling and chill.
When potatoes are done, mix together and refrigerate.
Serve well chilled.

title: mexican hot chicken(low-fat)
directions: Saute onion in pan.
Add chicken; pour into casserole.
Stir in tomatoes, soup and cheese; sprinkle taco shells on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Exchanges: 3 proteins, 1/2 vegetable and 25 optional calories.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and olives.
Spread thin layer of mixture on tortilla.
Arrange 4 slices of ham over cheese.
Tightly roll up tortilla.
Wrap individual in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Makes 64.

title: quick fried rice
directions: Steam celery and onions in large frying pan until tender.
Add roast beef and rice; heat and toss with soy sauce.

title: pear relish
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Grind (food grinder or chopper) the last 4 ingredients.
Pour in vinegar mixture and cook for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal tops.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until squash is tender; drain and mash. Combine squash, half of cracker crumbs, cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased baking dish (2-quart).
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: simple skillet salmon
directions: Cut steak in half lengthwise.
Cut away from bone and skin. Curl each strip of fish into a circle; fasten with 2 toothpicks. Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add fish.
Saute onion, garlic and ginger 2 minutes.
Turn fish over.
Add juice and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove fish to plate.
Season to taste.
Cover with sauce from pan.

title: creamy scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper in a large bowl with wire whip until foamy.
Beat in the cream or milk until smooth.
Heat the margarine in the top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Add the egg mixture and cook, stirring often, for 15 minutes or until eggs are creamy and set.
Serve immediately.
Make for New Years parties.

title: sweet lemon-onion relish
directions: Sweat onions in oil.
Squeeze juice from lemons and reserve. Cut rinds into 1/4-inch strips.
Put in small pan.
Cover with cold water; bring to boil.
Pour out water; repeat up to 3 times. When onions are tender, add drained lemon strips, juice, water, sugar, salt and thyme.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes, until liquid is reduced and onions and lemons are glazed.
Put up in glass jars; store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 3/4 cups (1 serving).
Serve with baked ham, lamb or chicken.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain ground meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup, picante sauce and cheese.
Heat to melt cheese.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg and sour cream alternately with combined dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add raisins.
Pour into a greased, fluted tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: feather pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir together until lumps disappear.
Bake on hot lightly greased griddle.
Makes 8 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Spoon can of fruit on top; do not mix in.
Do not add juice from can.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: stew beef chili
directions: Cut stew beef in small pieces.
Brown with onion in a little oil in large pot.
Add rest of ingredients except beans and rice. Mix well and simmer about 1 hour, adding more water if too thick. Add beans and heat until hot.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: dessert dip
directions: Mix together. Excellent for apple wedges, orange rings, pineapple chunks, banana chunks, kiwi fruit, etc.

title: zucchini bread casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick coating at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate pecan meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until frothy. Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in chocolate bits, nuts and vanilla. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto paper-lined cookie sheet. Bake at 300° about 25 minutes. Remove and store in airtight container. Makes approximately 36 meringues.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls and roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until set.
Remove immediately from a cookie sheet.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Wash and seed bell pepper.
Wash cabbage; core the cabbage. Using a food processor, shred the cabbage.
Put the shredded cabbage in a bowl.
Using the chopping blade, coarsely chop the bell pepper.
Combine the pepper with cabbage.
Next, pour in the dressing; stir.
Cover the bowl and refrigerate for several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cherry bread
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt; let cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, 1/2 c. cherry juice, eggs, vanilla, flour, cherries and remaining juice.
Mix until it forms a smooth, soft dough.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Mix down and let rise again until double in bulk.
Shape into 4 or 5 loaves.
Let rise until double.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Good toasted or with cream cheese.

title: polenta in crock-pot
directions: Grease sides of crock-pot set on high.
Add ingredients and stir well.
Cover and cook on high, 2 to 3 hours or on low for 6 to 9 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Before serving, you can add chunks of Mozzarella cheese and allow to melt.
(Serve with spaghetti sauce or stew.)
Serves 8 to 12.
(You can also add 2 mashed baking potatoes to mixture.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, 1/4 cup melted butter, salt and pepper and mix well.
Fold in thawed hash brown potatoes.
Put into prepared baking dish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and bananas and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Cool well and store overnight before chilling.
Very good served with softened cream cheese.

title: karen's potato salad
directions: Cut and boil potatoes until soft.
Drain and rinse.
In a large bowl mix olives and pickles.
Add mayo until consistency with what you want.
Do not mash potatoes, just stir them.
You will have some full chunks left in bowl.

title: chicken salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in warm stock.
Chill. Combine cayenne, vinegar, salt, celery and chicken.
When jello is slightly thickened, fold in chicken mixture.
Turn into loaf pan.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with mayonnaise. Serves 6.
(I used 1 jalapeno pepper, chopped extra fine.)

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Boil rice and salt in water.
Warm milk and canned milk; stir into cooked rice and add pudding, sugar, egg and raisins.
Bring to a boil and add vanilla and cinnamon.
Can be served either cool or warm.

title: speedy spinach lasagne
directions: Empty spaghetti sauce mix into saucepan; add tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Heat, stirring, until well blended. Remove from heat.

title: baked brie
directions: Saute almonds and garlic in butter until golden brown; place Brie in baking/serving dish; top with almond mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with crackers or slices of French bread.
Makes 2 to 4 appetizer servings.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Combine sugars, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture; fold in cereals.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll in small balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Makes 4 1/2 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda; let cool.
Add brown sugar, eggs, flour, butter and nuts.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix together and cook about 45 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese and fritos.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold in Cool Whip; fold into apple mixture and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until lightly browned.
Add ham and shrimp; cook until ham is light brown and shrimp is pink.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift the flour and dry ingredients together.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and sour cream.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until just blended.
Fold in raisins and caraway seed.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for about
50 minutes.
Rub a little butter over the top of the bread.
Happy St. Patrick's Day!

title: wild card chili
directions: Brown beef and onions, then drain off any fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in milk, juice and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking powder. Stir in small amounts at a time until all is used.
Stir in cherries and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pans.
Makes 2.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange bread
directions: Cut
orange peel into thin inch-long strips.
Add water and sugar.
Boil
together.
Cool.
Combine
egg
and milk and add to syrup.
Combine dry ingredients and add to liquid; mix. Permit to stand
for 10 minutes before baking.
Use loaf tin. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.
Cut with sharp knife.

title: monster cookies(serves 20 to 22 dozen cookies)
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs and add sugar, soda, vanilla and syrup.
Add margarine.
Mixing bowl will be full.
Add rest of ingredients, stirring with a large spoon.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: cherry torte
directions: Put part of mixture (all except cherries) on bottom of pan. Put cooked, sweetened and thickened cherries on mixture.
Cover with remaining top mixture.
Bake until brown on top, about 30 minutes, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans in colander and rinse until water runs clear.
In a glass jar, mix remaining ingredients and shake.
Place rinsed beans in dish; shake vinegar mixture and pour over beans.
Chill at least four hours, stirring several times.
This keeps well.
I double recipe for picnics and pot-luck dinners.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Mix salt and baking powder with flour.
Add soda to sour milk and combine with first mixture.
Add mashed bananas, flour, vanilla and nuts to batter.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: caramel apple breakfast rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix brown sugar and whipping cream in ungreased round pan, 8 x 1 1/2 inches, sprinkle with pecans. Unroll breadstick dough, but do not separate into breadsticks. Spread applesauce over dough. Roll up dough from short end; separate at perforations. Place coiled dough in pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minutes. Invert pan onto heatproof tray or serving plate. Let stand 1 minutes so caramel will drizzle over rolls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apples together.
Mix fruit, sugar and nuts together.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Mix well and place in refrigerator until well set.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Prepare patty shells according to package directions.
In a medium saucepan, heat butter until melted.
Add onion and garlic and cook until soft and transparent.
