Stir in flour, curry powder and salt and cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cream, beating until smooth.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes longer over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Stir in shrimp and cook until heated through.
Spoon shrimp mixture into warm patty shells and serve with chutney and coconut.

title: sunny banana shake
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients except cinnamon. Blend on high speed 1 minute or until smooth.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook green beans, lima beans and peas until done and layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook green pepper until tender and layer atop cooked vegetables.
Whip whipping cream.
Fold in mayonnaise and most of the Parmesan cheese.
Spread cream mixture over vegetables and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 15 minutes until heated thoroughly and golden brown.

title: ritz ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble Ritz crackers.
Add melted oleo and put in dish.
Mix pudding with the milk and ice cream.
Pour in dish and let stand 1 hour in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and toasted coconut.

title: baked beans
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Soak overnight.
Drain and put in large pot with water to cover.
Add chopped onion and salt pork.
Boil until tender, adding water as needed.
When cooked, but not mushy, place in greased casserole.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into pie crust and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then combine with dressing made with the last 4 ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to sugar mixture.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Pour batter into cake pan.
Put the nuts on top of raw batter and press into batter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325° and 1 more hour at 300°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and pour into baking dish.
Top with crushed Cheez-Its crackers.
Dot with 3/4 stick of oleo.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake in large flat pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast omelet
directions: Brown and scramble sausage; drain well.
Melt 1 tablespoon of margarine in skillet.
Beat eggs; pour into buttered skillet.
Put sausage or bacon on eggs; let eggs brown.
Fold over.

title: upside-down sundaes
directions: Roll ice cream balls in peanuts to coat; freeze until firm. Meanwhile, combine pudding mix, corn syrup and peanut butter. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Pour a generous amount of pudding mixture into individual dessert dishes.
Set peanut-covered ice cream ball atop.
If desired, garnish with frozen whipped dessert topping, thawed.
Serves 6.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage.
Add remaining ingredients. Season to taste with basil, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper. Simmer until vegetables are tender (great made in crock-pot).

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; stir in other ingredients.	Simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend until smooth, cream cheese and melted butter.
Add all other ingredients together well; set aside.
Open crescent rolls and make 4 squares.
Put 1/2 cup mixture in center of each square. Pinch centers together in center.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If precooked and frozen, 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable "aspic"(good)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chop celery and bell pepper in small pieces.
Drain and chop tomatoes well; save juice. Slice or chop onions fine.
Add juice and veggies after Jell-O has begun to thicken and mix well.
Really pleases men folk.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk and stir in whipped topping.
Add chocolate chips and mini marshmallows.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add chocolate syrup; mix.
Add flour; mix.
I use an electric hand mixer. Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: surprise cinnamon buns
directions: Mix 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Dip marshmallow halves into butter, then sugar. Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir in 2 tablespoons sugar, shortening and Bisquick.
Beat well. Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 20 times.
Divide dough into 12 pieces; flatten into 4-inch circles. Wrap each circle around marshmallow, pinching edges together tightly.
Dip into butter, then into sugar mixture. Place in 12 greased muffin cups. Cover and let rise 30 minutes. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: meat flavored onions
directions: Peel and core the onion.
The hole should be large enough for a bouillon cube. Fill the middle of the onion with butter or margarine.
Put the bouillon cube in the butter.
Wrap in aluminum foil and cook in the oven or on the grill until soft.

title: honduran rice
directions: Put oil in 2-quart pot. Add all other ingredients, except water. Saute, then add water. Stir until boiling; put lid on. Turn burner to medium and cook for 20 minutes. (Do not stir.) After done, crack lid and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: heart cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and orange peel in a large bowl until fluffy.
In a separate bowl, sift together next 3 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, mixing well.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in ovenproof casserole dish. Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: clam casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ovenproof serving dish, about size of roasting pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix warm water, sugar and yeast together.
Add oil, milk and soda.
Add flour and put mixture in a covered bowl for a few hours.
Stir lightly onto a floured surface.
Work with hands to form biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in three 8 x 8-inch pans or 1 long pan at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until well done.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine pudding, pineapple, sour cream and sugar in a deep bowl.
Beat with mixer at lowest speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell and chill at least 3 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Add juice from fruit cocktail to softened cream cheese and beat well with electric mixer.
Add fruit, cherries and marshmallows.
Blend well; add nuts if desired.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan and freeze.
Serves 8.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa and butter to a rolling boil in saucepan. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir well and place spoonfuls on waxed paper to cool. Enjoy!

title: layered salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Wash and drain lettuce. Add 1 layer of lettuce to bottom of container. Next, add 1 layer of chopped bell peppers, then a layer of (drained) English peas. Next, a thin layer of mayo, then cheese. Top with eggs, then bacon. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours prior to serving.

title: dark and stormy
directions: The national beverage of Bermuda.
Everyone who goes there comes away with a desire for this mixed drink.
A good way to use the remainder of the Gosling Black Rum.
Two ounces of black rum and 6 ounces of ginger beer over 2 pieces of ice in a glass.
Try this while you cook up a good meal and everything will fall in place.

title: oven goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
In medium skillet, combine ground beef, onion and celery.
Cook until beef is browned and celery is tender. Drain, if desired. Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese. Add macaroni.
Mix well. Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and mix until smooth. Add soda and flour to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add sweetened condensed milk and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas as usual.
Garnish with wafer crumbs.

title: walnut salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over favorite salad greens or cooked pasta.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder together.
Add butter, shortening, buttermilk and milk.
Roll dough and cut out biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 8-10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream soups and rice together.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer chicken (skin side up) in this mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 package Lipton dry soup mix over all.
Sprinkle 1/8 cup water over soup mix.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: aunt chata's "gallinitas"(game hens)
directions: Wash and, if desired, cut game hens down the middle; season with salt and pepper.
In a blender or processor, put onions cut in eighths, garlic cut in half, parsley well washed and prechopped, along with the juice of one lemon.
Process it all.
Leave mixture separate from the hens and proceed to sear or brown the game hens in a large skillet.
This may need to be done in two skillets or as many as fit in the pan at a time.

title: skillet chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken in hot oil in large skillet; remove and cut into bite-sized pieces.

title: sparkling rainbow melon
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except soda. Refrigerate until well chilled.
Add soda right before serving.

title: stuffing for chicken or turkey
directions: Cook hen and save broth.
Use hen for chicken salad, etc.
Mix all ingredients and stuff turkey or chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes to 1 hour. Before baking, you can put bread crumbs on top and bake according to directions.

title: pretzels
directions: Soften yeast in warm water in large bowl. Add butter, sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups of flour. Blend well. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. By hand, gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough. Knead dough for about 1 minute, until no longer sticky. Shape into a ball, cover and let raise in greased bowl in warm place about 45 to 60 minutes until doubled in size. Shape into pretzel shapes. Place on greased cookie sheets. Cover, let raise 30 minutes. Heat water and baking soda in 2 qt. pan. Gently drop pretzels into hot solution. Take out with a slotted spoon after they have floated to the top and then place on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with salt. Bake at 375 degrees for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: lemonade salad
directions: Mix well.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chill.
(Save 1/3 cup for topping.)
Mix by hand, Eagle Brand milk, thawed lemonade and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Sprinkle reserved crackers over top. Refrigerate.

title: party trash
directions: Melt and mix seasonings.
Let simmer 1
to
minutes. Spoon the fluid over the cereal and mix with
hands.
Place in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 225°.
Stir several times in open pan. If
you
add more
cereal, etc., then add
another
stick
of margarine.
Let cool and store in tight jars or
cans.
(I use Corn Chex instead of Wheat Chex.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes with butter and milk.
Blend in sour cream and dip.
Fold in bacon bits.
Place in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes at 300°.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal in a blender into a fine powder; set aside. Cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into balls and bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy wings
directions: Stir oil and soy sauce together.
Brush on wings.
Sprinkle on salts and powder; broil 10 minutes.
Mix vinegar, soup and brown sugar.
Baste and roast at 350°.
Turn once until done.
I have also put them in a crock-pot on low after they've been broiled.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake in oven at 400° until golden brown.
Remove from oven and let cool thoroughly.
Mix together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Spread on top of crust when cooled. Spread on top with pie filling.

title: arkansas sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and beef.
Pour off grease and set aside. Saute bell pepper
and
onion
in butter. Add jalapeno relish, picante sauce and
Velveeta
cheese.
Add meat.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir often.
(Can be put in the crock-pot.)

title: mom's sunday roast beef dinner
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.

Pat the meat dry with paper towels. Make slits into roast with tip of knife (not too deep, just thin enough and long enough to accomodate the garlic slices). Insert the slices of fresh garlic into the slits. Season the roast with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle (shake) the bottle of Maggi seasoning all over the roast (about 7 to 10 drops) straight from the bottle.
Open pouch of Lipton onion soup mix and pour some into a strainer and shake gently over the roast.
(You could use the dehydrated onion pieces, but they tend to burn during the roasting.
By straining the mix, you get all the flavor and you don't worry about burning little pieces of onion.) With a toothpick, secure the peeled, quartered onion pieces on top of the roast.
Place the meat on a roasting rack in a roasting pan.
Put it into the oven for 15 minutes.
Lower the oven temperature to 350° and continue to cook for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until a meat thermometer registers 120° for rare or 145° for well done.
(Depends on how you like your beef.)
Remove the meat from the oven.
Cover it with foil (to retain the heat) and let it rest in a warm place for 15 to 20 minutes before carving.
(By doing this you allow the juices to remain in the roast; if you immediately start to carve the roast, the juices of the meat will run out and your roast won't be as juicy at the table.)

title: ed's potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onion with chicken broth and enough water to cover; bring to boil until potatoes are tender.
Add instant potatoes and oleo to thicken.

title: eggplant or zucchini parmigiana
directions: Dice onion fine and saute in oil until soft.
Add the tomato sauce and all spices to the onions.
Bring to a very slight boil and let simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Remember, sauce should now be very tangy as the vegetables and cheese will later dilute this.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add eggs, one at a time; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Goes well in cupcake or tube pan also.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Form into small balls (walnut size); place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes for freezing.
(Can be made ahead of time and frozen), otherwise bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 dozen.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken (not overlapping).
Combine soup, sherry and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Cut 3 tablespoons margarine into flour.
Mix in cheese.
Add milk.
Melt stick of margarine in baking pan or muffin tins.
Add garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Drop biscuits in margarine and mix by tablespoon.
Brush tops with the margarine mix.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed.
Before cooling, cut slits in brownies and pour Kahlua over brownies to be absorbed into brownies.
Mix up instant pudding.
Use a large glass salad bowl or truffle dish (so you can see all the layers) Begin with 1/2 the brownies once cooled.
Spoon them into bowl, then 1/2 of the pudding, spreading evenly over top of the brownies.
Follow with 1/2 cool whip, spreading evenly.
Place the rest of the brownies evenly over the cool whip and repeat the process in the same manner.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over the top of the cool whip and using a knife cut through the top layer of cool whip to make a very impressive design.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture clings together; press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice; beat well.
Sift together 1/4 cup flour and baking powder; stir into egg mixture. Pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: crunchy oriental salad
directions: Crush Ramen noodles and brown lightly in butter with cashews. Chop broccoli well and lightly steam. Cool completely. Drain cashews and Ramen noodles on paper towels. Combine romaine lettuce, chopped green onions, broccoli, Ramen noodles and cashews in a bowl. Combine vegetable oil, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper. Blend well. Pour over salad mixture and toss. Serve immediately.

title: microwave mexican dip
directions: Brown and scramble sausage.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix in microwave container with cheese and tomatoes.
Microwave for 1 minute; stir.
Repeat until cheese is melted and well blended. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pecan sundae
directions: First Layer:
Mix together flour, butter and pecans.
Press into a square 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, 1/4 cup milk, margarine and vanilla for 1 minute; set aside.
Allow to cool.
Mix pudding and 3 cups milk in separate bowl.
Add Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers.
Cover with pudding mixture.
Place crackers on top of pudding mixture.
Pour icing on top.
Chill.

title: crab lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 15 minutes or per package directions.
Drain and cover with cold water.
Heat soup and crab together, mixing thoroughly.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain noodles.

title: russian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a baking dish.
Mix dressing and soup mix. Pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook, stirring until mixture thickens.
Cook 12 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Remove, arrange filling, bananas and wafers until dish is filled.
Top with meringue made from 3 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: sue's breakfast before(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Make the evening before.
Refrigerate and pop in the oven.

title: meat filling for pita
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas supreme
directions: In a saucepan, heat oil and brown the flour.
Dissolve chili powder in chicken stock from stewing chicken.
(Make up the difference with warm water, if you don't have 4 cups stock.) Season with garlic powder and salt.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered. Stir frequently until smooth and fairly thick.

title: 6 can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a large casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In large saucepot, heat oil; saute ground beef, onion and garlic, stirring often.
Add tomato paste, water, tomatoes (that have been forced through a sieve), seasonings, sugar and herbs. Simmer slowly 2 hours or longer; stir occasionally.
Taste and add additional seasonings, if required.
Add more water if necessary. Makes 8 quarts meat sauce.
Recipe may be doubled.
Grated Romano or Parmesan cheese for topping spaghetti.
Freshly grated cheese gives superior flavor.
Makes 24 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 1 cup liquid.
Bring to a boil; dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until thick but not set. Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into 2 quart serving bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: cream cheese and smoked salmon soup
directions: Place stock in kettle with salmon and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add spinach and half of the green onions; simmer another 5 minutes.
Mix cream cheese with 1/4 cup of the hot soup until smooth.
Stir into the soup to blend.
Serve hot, garnished with remaining green onions.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, chicken and rice.
Put in buttered casserole, 1 large or 2 small ones.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and lemon juice. Cover casserole with sauce and mix.
Put additional cheese on top and sprinkle with bread crumbs that have been mixed with curry powder.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Freezes, uncooked, for later use.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, pecans and strawberries.
Stir all ingredients together until moistened. Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
In large bowl, break eggs over apples.
Stir lightly with a fork.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil and nuts.
Stir good.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(Raisins may be added.)

title: bina swarup's garbanzo beans
directions: In a skillet, brown 1 chopped onion.
Add tomato and combined dry ingredients.
Simmer until you can smell the spices.
Add rinsed and drained garbanzo beans.
Heat.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon or lime juice just before serving.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Let the ice cream stand at room temperature for about 5 minutes to soften slightly. Combine the cinnamon, sugar and cornflake crumbs in a shallow pan. Using an ice cream scoop, make 4 balls of ice cream. Roll these balls in the crumb mixture to cover completely. Wrap in a piece of aluminum foil and freeze 5 hours.

title: bean salad dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: crabmeat stir-fry
directions: Saute green
onions
in oil and butter for two minutes. Stir in green pepper and mushrooms and cook for additional two minutes. Add
water
chestnuts,
rice and crabmeat.
Stir-fry until thoroughly heated.	Add seasoning and parsley and serve immediately.
Serves four.

title: oatmeal bake
directions: Mix together
oil, sugar and eggs.
Add oatmeal, baking powder, salt and
milk.
Pour
into
greased
9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30
minutes at 350°.
Serve with warm milk and cinnamon and sugar mix.

title: sausage and hot peppers
directions: In crock-pot, cut sausage in chunks (1 1/2-inch); pour hot peppers, juice and all, over top.
Cover and cook.

title: marinated potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in 1 to 1 1/2-quart microwave dish.
Sprinkle with water. Cover tightly and microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir, re-cover and microwave on High another 3 or 4 minutes until fork-tender. Cool.
Mix in celery, onion, pepper and black pepper. Stir in salad dressing. Cover tightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss gently before serving.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: In a greased 3 qt. baking dish layer the sausage, onions, mushrooms, tomatoes and cheese.
In a large bowl whisk the pancake mix, eggs, milk, oregano, salt and pepper, and pour over cheese.

title: don't know casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in butter.
Brown turkey meat; add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Prepare noodles as package directs.
Drain noodles and place in casserole dish.
Pour meat sauce over noodles.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
You may add some of the cheese to sauce as it cooks if you like.

title: hot mexican cornbread
directions: Stir all together except cheese.
Pour half the batter into a hot greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with half the cheese.
Pour remaining batter over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Grease baking dish and add contents.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: texas fruitcake
directions: Mix cherries and pineapple with flour.
Mix rest of ingredients with fruit and flour, except milk.
Dribble milk over mixture and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch bread pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish hamburgers
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Season with salt and pepper. Chop celery to make 1/2 cup.
Chop onion fine and combine with celery, bay leaves, garlic and brown sugar; add to meat with butter.
Combine and pour over meat, vinegar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Blend well. Simmer 45 minutes; then remove bay leaves and garlic.
Spread mixture on toasted hamburger buns.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and milk.
Beat until well blended. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls in batter and swirl around. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over hot cake.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt. Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to the pumpkin mixture.
Mix until well blended. Spread into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Makes 36 bars.

title: diabetic chocolate candy
directions: Place milk and chocolate in pan on stove.
Stir until melted. Add sugar, salt and Sweet 'N Low.
Stir and bring to a boil. Cook until soft.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Pour into pan.
When hard, cut into squares.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine corn and eggs; mix well. Combine flour, salt, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir into corn.
Add butter and milk.
Pour into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Set casserole dish inside a larger dish with hot water to gel the custard.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread as directed on package.
Crumble when cool and mix the rest of ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Put oranges through meat chopper.
Add juice and pulp from lemons and grapefruit.
Measure; add 3 cups water for each cup of fruit.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand until next day.
Next day, measure and allow 7/8 cup sugar for each cup of fruit.
Bring to boil.
Add sugar.
Cook rapidly until it will jell.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight; do not allow to rise. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear one loaf into large marble size pieces and drop helter skelter into pan.
Melt butter in pan and add brown sugar, pudding, milk and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth. Pour this over torn up loaf.
Tear second loaf and drop on top (trying to place in empty spots).
Let rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes and turn out on wax paper.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Add 1 1/2 gallons of water. Cook slowly until well done.
Add all ingredients.
Pour into baking pan and bake 5 or more hours at 350°.
If necessary, add more water while beans are baking.
This serves about 20.

title: lasagna(feeds 25)
directions: Mix hamburger into Spaghetti Sauce.
Mix cottage cheese with next 6 ingredients and part of Mozzarella cheese.
Layer sauce, noodles, cheese mixture, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Repeat until used up.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef, finely chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Remove all grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over hamburger rolls with melted cheese.

title: baked saurkeraut "n" rabbit
directions: Wash rabbit.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan; pepper and salt.
Pour water and sauerkraut over rabbit.
Add garlic.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Be sure to cover pan with Reynolds Wrap before cooking.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix and blend all cheeses and seasonings.
Form into roll and chill.
Tear dried beef into small bits.
Roll entire Cheese Roll in beef bits.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Combine rotini, broccoli, tomatoes, olives, onion and tuna; set aside.
Combine vinegar, lemon juice, water, olive oil, mustard and pepper in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over pasta mixture; toss gently before serving.
Yield:
6 servings; 147 calories (26% from fat) per 1-cup serving.

title: key lime cake
directions: Blend first five ingredients until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Saute steak and ground meat.
Mix together meat, onions, all seasonings and soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
At the last minute, add 1 cup warm sour cream.
Serve over rice, Chinese noodles or egg noodles.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; remove fat.
Mix in the seasoning and beans. Mix salsa and sour cream together.
In an ovenproof dish, layer the dish with hamburger mixture on the bottom.
Then layer the sour cream mixture and top with grated cheese to cover.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until cheese melts on top.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: tuna salad for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Good with crackers and potato chips.

title: swiss stuffed mushrooms
directions: Place mushroom caps top side up on baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Broil about 2 minutes.
Turn caps over and brush with melted butter.
Stuff by blending together remaining melted butter, bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Broil until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve with steaks.
Allow 2 caps per serving.

title: italian beef
directions: Bake roast seasoned with salt and pepper to taste in 350 F oven for 2 hours.
Remove from oven and let cool; slice in very thin slices.
Mix seasonings along with 2 cups of beef broth in crock pot and add sliced meat.
Simmer on low for 2 hours or until ready to serve.

title: natty rice loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray loaf pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Combine all ingredients.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brown on edges and firm to touch.
Serve warm or hot.

title: fresh fruit with ginger
directions: Finely chop ginger root in a food processor or shred using large holes of a cheese grater.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water into processor or put shredded ginger into a small bowl and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: pineapple glazed chicken
directions: For sauce, drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Combine pineapple, reserved syrup, chili sauce, sugar and mustard.
Brush chicken lightly with oil; season with salt.
Grill chicken over medium hot coals, bone side down, for 25 to 30 minutes or until bone side is well brown.
Turn chicken.
Grill 20 minutes more. Turn chicken again.
Spoon sauce on top.
Grill 5 to 10 minutes more or until chicken is done.
Makes 12 servings.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Clean chicken and boil with seasoning salt and pepper.
Cut 1 whole onion up into water with chicken.
Cook until chicken is good and tender.
Take chicken and remove from bones.
Take a medium-size Pyrex dish; add chicken to the bottom, then add cream of mushroom with a 1/2 cup of the broth from the chicken.
Mix together.
Take the peas, string beans, carrots and corn.
Combine all ingredients.
Take the Ritz crackers and crumble over the top of dish.
Put in oven and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: macaroni soup
directions: Brown stew beef, cut into small pieces, in fat.
Add onion and cook slowly until transparent.
Add celery and then add enough water to cover beef well.
Add bouillon cubes and simmer until beef is very tender.
Add canned tomatoes (including juice) and macaroni.
Heat and serve.
A good soup for winter!

title: batter for onion rings and other veggies
directions: Mix altogether.
If batter is too thick, add more milk.
It too thin, add a little more flour.
Dip sliced onions or other vegetables in and deep fry to a golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to a boil; remove from heat.
Add to soup: gelatin, water and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add to soup mixture: onion, celery, mayonnaise and shrimp.
Mix well.
Pour ingredients into mold sprayed with nonstick spray.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Turn out mold onto large plate.
Garnish with parsley, sliced almonds for fish scales and stuffed olive slice for fish eye.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon and onion until soft.
Smooth lumps with fork.
Add cocktail and Worcestershire sauces until pink; add crab meat last.
Form into ball and place on serving plate.
Use remaining cocktail sauce to spread on the top.
Finger like frosting.
Chill and serve on any crackers.
Can mix 1/2 shrimp and 1/2 crab.

title: bavarian brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, milk, egg and margarine.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 36 bars.

title: curried shrimp in avocado halves
directions: Brush avocado halves with lime juice.
Place in shallow baking pan.
(You may want to cut a thin slice off bottom of each avocado half to steady it.)
Heat for 10 minutes in slow oven (300°).
In saucepan, combine butter or margarine, curry powder and salt. Stir in tomato and onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add shrimp; heat through.
Blend in sour cream; heat through, but do not boil.
Spoon into warm avocado halves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Pour into oblong pan and shape.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Or place into a microproof ring mold and cook on High in microwave 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, salt, eggs and vinegar.
Add coconut, nuts and raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: beef taco bake
directions: In skillet over medium to high heat, cook beef until brown, stirring to separate meat. Drain well to get rid of fat. Once this is done, add soup, salsa, milk, tortillas and half the cheese. Spoon into 2-quart shallow baking dish and cover. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and serve.

title: aunt dorothy's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven at 325 degrees.
Mix all ingredients, pour in prepared tube pan, and bake 30 minutes, then reduce oven to 300 degrees and bake for another 40 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except sour cream together.
Pour half of	this
mixture
in
a bowl; congeal, leaving the other half sitting
out.
When first part has congealed, spread sour cream on this
and
then
pour rest of Jell-O over sour cream. Let congeal.

title: idiot fudge
directions: Melt ingredients together.
Mix in 1 pound or 3 1/2 cups 10x sugar.
Press into ungreased pan and cut by refrigerating.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: stove top applebutter
directions: In large kettle put all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Stir for 20 minutes.
Put in jars.
Yield:
6 - 6 1/2 pints.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add celery and onion; cook about 4 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in next 5 ingredients until well blended.
Add chicken, almonds and mushrooms; toss to coat well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yellow zucchini cake
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed (electric mixer) for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
If baked in a Bundt pan, bake 40 to 45 minutes or until tester comes clean.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar icing.

title: vinegar cake(nicknamed "ol' sudden")
directions: Cream the sugar and oil together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix together.
Add flour, one cup at a time, and blend well each time (5 minutes).
Makes a large cake or fun cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add bread crumbs and butter to scalded milk.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole in shallow pan of water at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and store in jar in the refrigerator overnight.

title: home style roast squab
directions: Cook in thin layers in a lightly greased pan.
If you use nori, make each sheet 4 x 7-inches.
Use any of the following ingredients as a filling:

title: german red cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage and fry in butter on low.
Mix in all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of batter into hot, greased pan.
Cover with half of cheese.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle the rest of the cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Mix together flours, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oats.
Add oil, eggs, bananas and blueberries (if using frozen blueberries, do not thaw).
Stir just until mixed.
Pour batter into two oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for approximately 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Wrap and refrigerate several hours before slicing.
Yields 2 loaves, 16 slices each.
Serving size:
1 slice.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Drain corn, beans and pimento.
Thoroughly mix all vegetables, soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish. Top with crushed crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked stuffed shrimp wellington
directions: Peel shrimp leaving shell next to tail.
Cut inside shrimp halfway through (clean).
Make Stove Top stuffing per recipe. Dice Surimi and garlic.
Add Tabasco and Worcestershire and saute in butter.
Add stuffing and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Take cold stuffing and stuff cut shrimp.
Wrap stuffed shrimp with pastry sheet, leaving seam on bottom.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until pastry is golden brown.
Serve with sauteed mushrooms. Serves 4.

title: savory vegetable beef soup
directions: Remove all fat from meat.
Boil until tender. Add water, if necessary. Remove from heat and strain broth.
Refrigerate broth overnight.
Skim off fat and heat.
Add all vegetables which have been washed and chopped.
Add spices and macaroni. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and beet liquid or water. Place over low heat and stir sauce until it is clear and thickened.
Add beets and heat thoroughly.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beating well after each. In another container (or on wax paper), sift dry ingredients. Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto prepared cookie sheet.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Put peppers in large pot, cover with water and bring to boil. When water reaches boiling point, turn off flame and let peppers stay in water 5 minutes; drain and cool.
Cut the top inch off, saving tops.
Remove seeds and membranes and rinse peppers.
While peppers are being prepared, grate 1 onion.
Mix together beef, rice, grated onion, beaten egg, salt, Tabasco sauce and 3 tablespoons cold water.
Stuff peppers with the mixture and put aside.
Heat salad oil in pot in which peppers were scalded. Saute 2 sliced onions in oil until golden, but not crisp.
Add stewed tomatoes and then place peppers (with tops put back on) in the sauce.
Spoon some sauce over peppers.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, add thawed fruit.
Pour over top of pretzel mixture and let cool in refrigerator for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken breast delight
directions: Mix all but chicken well.
Grill breasts on one side 2 minutes; turn and coat with mixture.
Continue to turn and coat until center of breasts lose the pink color.
Total time: 10 to 12 minutes.
Good warmed in microwave for a sandwich the next day.

title: zucchini parmesan(microwave)
directions: Melt oleo in casserole pan; add seasonings and mix with sliced zucchini.
Cover.
Microwave on High power 4 to 5 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and let stand for 2 minutes.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Pour jello in bowl.
Add boiling water.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Pour 1 cup cold water into a 2 cup measuring cup.
Add enough ice and water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Add to jello and stir until slightly thickened.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes more. Stir in sliced bananas.
Spray a 4 cup jello mold with Pam.
Pour jello mix into mold.
Refrigerate until firm (2 hours).
Dip mold in warm water and invert on plate.
Fill with fresh fruit.

title: cajun quick fix
directions: Slice pork chops into strips; brown in oil.
Add chopped celery and frozen corn; simmer for about 3 minutes.
Stir in can of tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes. To make it really Cajun style, I add 1/2 to 3/4 pound sliced smoked sausage.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese and bacon bits in a large serving bowl.

title: snappy turtles
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add 1 egg and 1 egg yolk; mix well. Add dry ingredients and vanilla; mix well.	If dough is soft after
mixing,
refrigerate
until	firm.
Pinch
off
a teaspoonful at a
time
and
make a small ball.
Dip ball in 1 beaten egg	white.	Place on greased cookie sheet over 3 pecan halves to
look
like
a turtle.
Put chocolate icing on after cooling.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Saute sausage, green pepper and onion until sausage is done. Drain and place in 2-quart baking dish.
Add beans, brown sugar and barbecue sauce; mix well.
Place bacon strips on top and bake 1 hour in 375° oven.
Let cool for about 30 minutes before serving.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; add onions.
In a quart casserole dish, layer bottom with tortilla chips.
Add ground beef.
Sprinkle beef with a thin layer of taco seasoning.
In a small bowl, mix cream of mushroom and Ro-Tel together, then pour on top of beef. Sprinkle with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Layer with lettuce and tomatoes (if desired).

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; cook over medium heat, stirring often while it comes to a boil.
Then cook without stirring until a drop forms a firm ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites; pour about half of the hot syrup mixture into the egg whites while beating constantly.
While remaining syrup continues to cook, add vanilla and salt to egg mixture.

title: parmesan potato wedges
directions: Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray. Combine Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Cut each potato into 8 wedges. Put in bag with dry ingredients and shake until coated. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until browned and tender. Yields 4 servings.

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: deneen's chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken and broth into a pan with the potatoes, celery, carrots and onions. Bring to a boil.
Add mustard.
Stir in cornstarch. When vegetables are tender, pour over pie crust that has been placed into casserole dish.
Put remaining pie crust on top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and shortening.
Add sugars gradually until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese or Burnt Sugar Icing.

title: five bean soup
directions: Do not drain beans.
Mix all ingredients in large pan.
Add 2 cans of water.
Simmer approximately 1 hour on low.
Will freeze.

title: overnight buns
directions: Boil 4 cups water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Pout in 1 cup melted lard.
Cool good!!
Beat eggs, salt and 1 cup flour.
Put 1 package yeast in lukewarm water; when water is cool, mix everything together.
Add flour a little at a time, kneading dough.
Dough should be slightly sticky.

title: pork tenderloins with blackberry mustard sauce(cooking light)
directions: Prepare Blackberry Mustard and set aside.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon minced thyme and next 5 ingredients. Trim fat from pork. Rub pork with thyme mixture. Chill in shallow covered dish 2 hours. Coat large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.

Add oil. Place over medium-high heat until hot. Cook pork 4 minutes until brown on all sides. Add 1/4 cup broth and vinegar to skillet; bring to boil. Cover; reduce heat. Simmer 25 minutes (meat thermometer 160°). Remove pork. Keep warm. Add remaining 1 cup broth
and sugar to skillet. Boil 5 minutes; strain.

Place cornstarch in small pan. Gradually add water; blend. Stir in strained mix and 1/4 cup Blackberry Mustard. Boil; stir constantly 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining 1 teaspoon minced thyme. Spoon sauce on plates. Cut pork 1/2-inch slice.
Serve with berries and thyme sprigs (optional).

title: blueberry cream muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, oil and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream to egg mixture.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: oyster soup(microwave)
directions: Season oysters with pepper and frizzle in their own juice in a 2-quart dish until edges are slightly curled, 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Set aside.
Micromelt butter in an 8-cup measure.
Add flour and onion,
Saute on High 3 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add mushroom soup, oyster liquid and milk.
Mix well after each ingredient.
Microwave on High 6 minutes; stir at 2 minute intervals.
Add drained oysters, salt and onion tops to hot milk mixture.
Serves 6.

title: three cheese noodle bake(healthy recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch) with nonstick spray.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain. Mix noodles and remaining ingredients.
Spread in dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until center is set and edges are golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla and beat vigorously about 2 minutes.
Fold in blueberries.
Combine nutmeg, sugar and pecans.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve warm or cold.
Freezes well.

title: dressing
directions: Boil chicken and debone; add other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sausage and egg casserole(main dish for breakfast or brunch)
directions: Arrange half of bread in a single layer in bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Crumble and cook sausage in a skillet until lightly browned; drain grease.
Grate cheese.
Sprinkle all sausage and cheese over bottom layer of bread in baking dish.
Top sausage and cheese with another layer of bread slices.
In a bowl, beat eggs, salt, pepper and mustard until blended; add milk.
Pour mixture over bread, filling the dish.
Let sit at least 1 hour at room temperature.
(It can sit overnight or longer in the refrigerator.)
Bake in preheated oven at 375 degrees about 30 minutes or until light brown.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving. Amounts can be increased or decreased easily depending on the number of people being fed.

title: crushed pear salad
directions: Heat pear juice and pour over Jell-O.
Then mix with cream cheese and milk.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Cool, then mix with pears.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
Saute in olive oil with shallots and garlic.
Add the rest of the ingredients, then simmer the chicken, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve with angel hair pasta (cooked).

title: carrot casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking 45 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Combine ingredients. Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and use for a filling between the layers, reserve 1 cup of mixture for frosting.

title: pazczki
directions: Bring water to boil with the butter.
Add flour gradually, mixing constantly, until the butter forms a ball.
Remove from stove and cool.
Add salt and granulated sugar and beat in eggs one by one.
Form round balls, greasing your hands in melted butter each time and fry in hot deep fat under cover, on a low flame for about 15 minutes or until evenly browned, turning once.
Drain on absorbent paper in a warm place.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: italian coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage on sliced side of grater.
Place in a large bowl in layers with thinly sliced onions.
Top with 3/4 cup sugar.
In a saucepan combine vinegar, oil, 4 tablespoons sugar, celery seed, salt and dry mustard.
When mixture comes to a boil, remove from heat and pour over cabbage and onions.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Cook on 450° until golden brown.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put milk onto heat (keeping out small amount for later use). Put chocolate in heating milk.
Mix flour, salt and sugar (sift together).
Stir into dry mixture melted butter and egg yolks.
To make batter more workable, add small amount of milk that was held out.
When milk is scalded, pour in batter slowly, stirring until it thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: lentil roast
directions: Cook lentils until quite dry, salting during cooking.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This roast makes good sandwich filling cold.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add 1 cup more of milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly with rotary beater 1 minute.
Pour at once into 9-inch crumb crust.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cottage cheese and spinach salad
directions: Dressing:
In a small mixing bowl stir together the sour cream, sugar, horseradish, dry mustard and salt.
Using a wire whisk, gradually blend in the herb-flavored vinegar.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator until serving time.
At serving time, place spinach in large salad bowl.
Spoon the cream-style cottage cheese on top of spinach in a ring.
Sprinkle walnuts on top of cheese.
Pour on the dressing and toss lightly until spinach is coated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green and gold vegetable casserole
directions: Layer green beans, corn, water chestnuts and onion in casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and milk.
Spread over top of vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and simmer until soft. Strain through a sieve.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and mustard. Boil again for 30 minutes.
Seal hot in bottles.

title: creamy southwest noodles
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, stir together sour cream and taco seasoning over low heat until warm.
Serve sauce over pasta.
Top with picante sauce, cheese and olives.

title: spaghetti
directions: Prepare sauce as with lasagne.
Onion, mushrooms and bay leaves may be added, if desired. Boil spaghetti according to package directions until soft. Drain and mix with olive oil to prevent clumping.
Serve sauce over noodles.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop onion, pepper, celery, pimentos and sauerkraut.
Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.

title: pork chop creole(a delicious 45-minute meal)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet with tight fitting cover.
Roll thinly cut pork chops in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot oil. Slice potatoes and onions.
Remove chops.
Add layer of potatoes and onions.
Add hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Return chops to skillet.
Simmer in tightly covered skillet 30 minutes.
Add sliced green pepper and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: three-bean salad
directions: The day before, if desired, drain beans and place in a glass bowl.
Add onion.
Mix oil and vinegar with sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over bean mixture.
Toss and refrigerate, covered, until served.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with nuts.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Measure and sift together 3 times: cake flour, cocoa and 7/8 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Measure egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla into large mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer (on high) until foamy throughout.
Add the 3/4 cup sugar gradually, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat 10 seconds after each addition. Continue beating until meringue is firm and holds stiff, straight peaks when knife or spatula is gently lifted out of meringue.

title: zucchini corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased pan 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: jerry's quick and easy cookies
directions: Heat milk, butter and vanilla. Stir in cocoa and sugar.
When sugar is dissolved, let boil for 1 to 2 minutes. Be careful not to let it burn.
Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter and stir. Stir in cereal to coat. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: hungarian pepper dish
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add onion; cook over moderate heat until wilted.
Add green peppers; cook until crisp tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cook covered over low heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Taste for seasoning.
Serve in vegetable dishes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pea surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased casserole dish at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with fried onions or bread crumbs.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until dissolved.
Stir over medium heat until 278° on candy thermometer and add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; butter hands and form balls.

title: kenya yams
directions: Peel and cut up yams into deep casserole.
Pour on coconut milk.
Sprinkle on brown sugar.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: quick barbecue chicken
directions: Skin your chicken.
This cuts down on fat and cholesterol. Pour half the bottle of barbecue sauce in a large stew pot.
Place chicken in pot and pour remaining sauce on top.
Bring to a slow simmer and cook for approximately 40 minutes.
Serve with rice and biscuits.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon into lightly greased loaf pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cut into slices to serve.
Serves 4.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine shortening and sugar; cream well.
Blend in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Add pecans, dates and cherries; mix well.
Shape into balls using a level tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Crush corn flakes; mix with brown sugar.
Roll each ball of dough in corn flake mixture. Place on greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 maraschino cherry.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not stack or store until cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Blend in cooking oil until mixed well.
Beat in eggs on high speed until smooth 2 to 3 minutes.
Add pumpkin; beat 1 minute more.
Pour in slightly greased oblong pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Bake at 350°.

title: festival rice
directions: In a large frying pan, heat oil and saute onion, green pepper and celery until soft. Add mushrooms, sage, marjoram, thyme and vinegar.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetable mixture with green onions and rice.
Stir in half the nuts and half the cheese.
Spoon into a 2 1/4-quart ovenproof casserole dish. Sprinkle top with remaining nuts, cheese and parsley.
Heat through for 15 or 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix cranberry, lime and orange juices.
Chill thoroughly. When ready to serve, add the ginger ale and thin slices of lime. Serves 20.

title: grandma's apple muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and cloves. Add apples and walnuts; toss to coat. In small bowl, beat eggs with fork; beat in buttermilk and butter. Add to flour mixture. Stir just until blended. Fill greased tins 2/3 full. Sprinkle with Streusel Topping. Bake in preheated 400° oven until pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 15 to 25 minutes for muffins or 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch square.

title: three cheese manicotti
directions: Blend tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and 1 1/2 cups water. Meanwhile, combine 1 cup of the Mozzarella, the cottage cheese and Parmesan.
Add eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly. Stuff manicotti shells with cheese mixture, using about 1/4 cup for each.
Pour 1/2 cup of the sauce mixture into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange manicotti in dish; pour remaining sauce atop.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Add cheese spread to hot rice.
Add broccoli (partially thawed).
Add soup and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: danika's wheat and oat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients except flours.
Mix well.
Add flours one cup at a time.
Knead or dough hook for 10 minutes.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Punch down dough and shape into loaves or small balls for rolls.
Place in pans; let rise for 30 minutes.
For shiny crust, brush a thin topping of beaten egg onto the top of rolls or loaves.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes for rolls, 40 minutes for loaves.

title: soy marinated swordfish
directions: Tuna may be substituted for swordfish.

title: meat soup
directions: In 8-quart pot, put 6 quarts of water.
Wash meat in cold water and add to pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.
Add quartered turnip and simmer 30 minutes.
Add quartered carrots and quartered potatoes.
Quarter cabbage and place on top of everything in the pot.
Cover for 30 minutes.
Serve with muffins or sourdough bread.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Put diced apple in dough and pull up sides to form a pouch and pinch together at the top.
Place in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix margarine (melted) and sugar and spoon on top of each pouch.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour 7-Up into pan, cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: dry barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in shaker and sprinkle over meats to cook.
Add to soup.
Add to all things you want to add for flavor.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Make rice as you would regularly, but adding 1 packet of sazon to the water per cup of rice.
(Use a little less water with the rice so it will come out firmer than usual).

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter together.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.
Pour batter into greased pan and bake in preheated oven at 275° for 1 hour.

title: slow cooker chili con queso
directions: To make the first batch, mix cheese, chili, onions, chili peppers and chips.
Cook on low for approximately 2 hours.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Blend with cream cheese and pears in blender.
Let set.
Then beat in 1/2 container Cool Whip.

title: philadelphia classic new york cheesecake
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press into bottom of 9 inch spring form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Mix next four ingredients with electric mixer until well blended.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is almost set if using silver spring form pan.
Loosen cake from side of pan.
Cool before removing rim of pan.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Makes 16 servings.
Prep. time 15 minutes plus refrigerating.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat together sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs; add to dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chicken terrific
directions: Combine chicken, rice, pimento, mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, water chestnuts, soups and green beans.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Combine stuffing and butter; mix thoroughly and spoon on top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken, cut into pieces.
Place in bottom of 3-quart pan.
Mix sour cream and all soups together.
Pour Veg-All over chicken.
Pour soup mixture over all of this.
Top with Waverly Wafers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: bubble soap
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make bubble blowers from a straw, a kitchen funnel or a thin wire shaped in creative forms.

title: meat loaf and veggies
directions: Coat a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.
Saute cabbage, celery, onion and garlic in oil in a large skillet until lightly browned and softened.
Stir often. Add 1 or 2 tablespoons of water if veggies seem dry.
Remove to plate and cool almost to room temperature.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Whisk all ingredients in a 3-quart microwave casserole dish until smooth.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap; microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Reduce to Medium-high; microwave 10 minutes longer.
Stir halfway through. Let stand 20 minutes, covered.
Yield 5 cups, 8 servings. Calories: 112.
Fat: 0.

title: veal scaloppine with mushrooms
directions: Place the veal between sheets of waxed paper and pound pieces with the side of a cleaver until 1/4-inch thick, being careful not to tear the veal.
Dip the meat into the seasoned flour, shaking off excess.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: In a bowl, combine confectioners sugar, coconut, nuts, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, margarine or butter and vanilla. Take small pieces of dough and shape into 1 1/2-inch logs. Place on tray; cover and chill in the refrigerator overnight. Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler. Dip logs into chocolate and place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Store in cool place. Makes 50 to 60 logs.

title: cheesecake tart
directions: Mix flour, butter and water.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and sugar; add Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled tart.
Spread pie filling on top.

title: mountain berry pie
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, salt, cornstarch and cinnamon if desired.
Stir in berries.
Add water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat just to the boiling point.
Pour into pie shell; dot with butter.
Top with a lattice or full crust.
If using a full crust, cut slits in the top, brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until the crust is golden.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and cut spinach into bite size pieces.
Mix together mayonnaise, horseradish, vinegar and sour cream; pour sauce mix over spinach and cheese.
Mix well and chill.

title: mexican rice
directions: Wash rice in a small bowl and drain.
In a medium skillet, heat oil and add rice, stir until rice is a golden brown.
Add diced tomatoes and onion; stir for about 1 minute or 2.
Add tomato sauce and water or chicken broth. Season with garlic and salt to taste. Reduce heat and cover until rice is done.

title: after easter casserole
directions: Prepare white sauce by melting butter in saucepan. Stir in flour and cook until mixture bubbles. Add milk, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt and onion. Cook until thickened. Add grated cheese and stir until melted.

title: mulled cider
directions: Prepare both juices as usual except substitute 1 can of water for a can of rum. Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix together and roll in little balls; mash with a fork on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to a boil, then cook on low heat until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Cool, then heat until thick enough to spread on cake.
Add a little powdered sugar if it does not get thick enough.
Also, add vanilla.

title: cheese cake
directions: Press rolls in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan to form bottom crust. Beat all other ingredients (except eggs) until light and creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Pour mixture over rolls. Top with cinnamon and raisins, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Refrigerate.

title: hot wings
directions: Get oil hot.
Add cut up chicken wings and fry until they're done and floating.
In small saucepan heat butter and hot sauce until barely bubbling.
When wings are done, take them directly to hot sauce and simmer for 5 minutes, then serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook strawberries, sugar, salt and cornstarch until thick. Spread 1/2 large package softened cream cheese in shell. Place sliced strawberries over cream cheese. Put thickened strawberries over sliced strawberries. Cover with whipped cream. Garnish with strawberries.

title: calie persimmon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry delight #2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans in a bowl.
Mix well and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate chips over hot water and set aside.
Beat egg whites with a dash of salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar. Fold in chocolate and walnuts.

title: norwegian blotkake(wet cake)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light or pale yellow in color. Combine flour and baking powder; stir in slowly (add gradually). Stir in almond extract.
Pour batter into a 9-inch buttered and floured spring-form pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow pan.
Cover with mushrooms. Combine undiluted mushroom soup, sherry and sour cream.
Stir until blended.
Pour over chicken, completely covering it. Dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried rice with shrimp
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Add carrots, onion, shrimp and mushrooms. Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Pour in beaten eggs and stir until set. Add rice.
Add pepper.
Add peas and soy sauce.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and blend well.
Turn into balls the size of walnuts.
Place meatballs in 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan. Heat rest of ingredients in saucepan slowly until cranberry sauce is melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour sauce on meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.
Serve in chafing dish with toothpicks.
Makes about 85 meatballs.
(Roll meatballs in paper towel to drain grease.)

title: j. j.'s corn-on-the-cob
directions: In saucepan, melt butter or margarine; stir in mustard, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and lemon pepper.
Place each ear of corn on a 12 x 9-inch piece of heavy-duty foil; drizzle butter mixture over corn.
Fold edges of foil to seal pouch securely, leaving space for expansion of stem.
Grill over medium hot coals, turning occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fingerprint cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Cut in margarine. Sprinkle with vanilla.
Mix dough with hands until smooth.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Then roll in remaining nuts, lightly pressing to coat.

title: escarole soup
directions: In large soup or spaghetti pot, heat oil.

Add minced onion; saute lightly, just until onion is transparent (about 5 minutes). Add tomatoes, beef broth, escarole and all seasonings; cook, uncovered, over medium heat until tomatoes are cooked down and escarole is tender, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 4 servings.
Good in summer!

title: crustless zucchini pie
directions: Peel zucchini and grate.
Mix first 5 ingredients. Stir in zucchini and Bisquick and cheese.
Spray 8 x 8 dish or deep pie dish.
Bake at 350° till knife comes out clean.
(I use Kraft green can Parmesan cheese.)

title: spaghetti and hamburger
directions: Boil the spaghetti in salted water for about 12 minutes; do not drain.
Fry hamburger and onions together until hamburger is brown.
Then pour into spaghetti and tomatoes.
Cook for about 20 minutes.

title: creamy apricot salad
directions: Combine gelatin and pineapple in saucepan; bring to boiling point.
Add sugar, apricot puree and cream cheese; simmer until cream cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat to cool.
Chill until partially congealed.
Chill milk in freezer tray until ice crystals form around edge.
Whip until stiff peaks form.
Fold into apricot mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Yields 15 servings.

title: cream cheese snowflake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and cream cheese well. Add sugar and beat in egg yolk, vanilla and orange rind.
Sift flour with salt and cinnamon; add to cream mixture.
Fill cookie press and make cookies using different shapes.
Decorate with colored sugar or red or green sparkles before baking.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: mandarin orange salad(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Place sour cream in medium bowl. Add all fruit and mix.
Add miniature marshmallows and coconut last. Chill.

title: cheese apple
directions: Bring to room temperature in mixing bowl all ingredients. Blend together with fork.
Set in refrigerator to solidify.
Form into ball and set on serving tray. Cover with paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients (for softer cookies, add 1/2 cup flour).
Drop dough by rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix the flour, garlic salt, m.s.g., paprika, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Beat
the egg in the milk.
Roll the chicken nuggets in flour mixture, dip in milk and roll back in flour mixture. Fry at 350° in Crisco.

title: low calorie corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, stir together the dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine the wet ingredients. Combine the ingredients of the two bowls and gently stir only until they are completely mixed.
Turn into a lightly oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Good with fried or baked fish.

title: chocolate pudding surprise
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour and butter.
Put in bottom of 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake until brown at 325°, then cool.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon, and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, salt, 1/3 stick margarine, vanilla, sugar, eggs and milk with beater.
Pour into greased pan. Mix together pecans, flour, brown sugar and 6 tablespoons margarine and put on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: garlic mushrooms
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet until very hot and stir-fry the mushrooms and garlic over high heat for 2 minutes.
Lower the heat and stir in the lemon juice, sherry, broth, paprika, chili pepper, salt and pepper.
Simmer a minute or two and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Scoop out stems and chop, then saute in butter until soft while mushroom stems and pieces are sauteing.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl.
Make sure to pulverize crackers first. Add mushroom pieces and stems to other ingredients and mix well. If dry, you may add a little water or butter.
Spoon filling into mushroom caps.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° oven in lightly greased pan.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix ingredients, together and roll into small balls and let stand until firm.
(Chill.)

title: poppy seed cups
directions: Trim the ends off bread slices.
Arrange each slice of bread in the cup of a muffin pan to form a bread cup.
Drizzle or brush butter on the edges of the bread and a small amount in the center of each cup.
Sprinkle or spoon poppy seed onto the buttered bread edges.
Toast in a hot oven at 425° until edges are brown.
Cool and remove from the pan.
Place chicken, ham, and/or tuna salad in each cup.
Very pretty and delicious.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain all cans of vegetables.
Mix all together in a large bowl.
Make dressing and pour over vegetables.
Let marinate at least 2 hours.
Better the next day.

title: tang-o mango sipper
directions: Blend undrained mango slices until smooth.
Stir in ginger ale.
Place ice cubes in tall glasses.
Pour juice mixture over ice and serve.

title: sausage strata deluxe
directions: Cook sausage in skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring frequently to break up into small pieces.
Coat bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been coated with vegetable spray. Spread croutons over bottom of pan.
Drain sausage well and spread over croutons.
In large bowl, whisk together eggs, soup, milk, mustard and rosemary.
Stir in spinach, cheese and mushrooms. Pour over sausage.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, preheat oven to 350°, uncover and bake about 1 hour or until set and lightly browned on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain, saving liquid.
Saute onions in margarine.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients, except crackers. Add 3/4 cup of liquid from broccoli; may use more if necessary for good consistency.
Put in greased casserole dish and sprinkle Ritz crackers over mixture.
Dot with a little margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Chop artichokes finely and add rest of ingredients.
Put another 1/2 cup shredded parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees F. Serve hot with crackers.

title: microwave campbell's classic family meat loaf
directions: Microwave:
In bowl mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, crumbs, onion, 3 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce, egg and pepper.
In a 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish, firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf. Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes or until firm in center, rotating dish twice during cooking.
Reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Let stand, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: zucchini hot cakes
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet (or use Pam or small amount of oil).
Beat eggs and other ingredients together.
Spoon 2 heaping tablespoonfuls into skillet.
Cook, over medium heat, until brown on both sides.

title: no bake cocoa orange balls
directions: Combine thoroughly all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered or granulated sugar.
Store in tight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: butterscotch noodles
directions: Melt chops over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Add noodles to the mixture.
Remove from heat and stir until all noodles are covered.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Place in refrigerator until hard.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot orange juice.Add water and chill until syrupy.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Fold in cool whip and cottage cheese.
Mold in 9x13 pan.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon.
Makes about 10 to 12.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix soup mix with mayonnaise, sour cream and chestnuts.
Drain spinach until all liquid is gone.
Mix in spinach.
Slice top off bread, pull out remaining bread from inside to form a bowl.
Put dip into bread right before serving.
