Cut bread you pulled out from the inside into cubes and arrange around the bread bowl to be used as dippers.

title: venison chili
directions: Cook meat thoroughly; drain off drippings.
Add beer and bouillon soup.
Mix in remainder of ingredients and allow to simmer 4 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Boil broccoli and onion in chicken broth until tender.
Drain. Melt butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add cream or milk, making a sauce.
Stir constantly.
Add drained broccoli and onion.
If too thick, add milk.
Stir in cheese and heat over very low heat until melted.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet.
Set off the stove.
Layer the remaining ingredients in order listed.
Cook over medium heat, covered for about 30 minutes until hamburger is done.

title: f~b~c~k favorite party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve!

title: farina torte(this serves 12 persons; swedish dish)
directions: Note: If you use a Pyrex pan, reduce oven to 325°.

title: impossible peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls, using 1 teaspoonful of dough.
Press on greased cookie sheet with fork. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour into bowl.
Make a hole in the middle of the flour. Add sugar.
Pour in milk.
Mix with a spoon until well mixed.
Add Crisco and mix. Turn mixture onto floured surface and knead with hands. Roll out smooth and cut out biscuits.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter flavored
Crisco in pan before placing biscuits in pan.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Spread sauerkraut and liquid over butter.
Sprinkle with rice, then onion, then ground beef, salt and pepper.
Top with sauce (use plenty of sauce).
Cook, covered, over low heat for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve in skillet. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheesecup cupcakes
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients and beat until smooth.
Put a vanilla wafer cookie in bottom of cupcake tins lined with papers.
Fill 2/3 full with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling when ready to serve.
Makes 14 to 16 cupcakes.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water until completely diluted. Add pineapple juice and freeze in large container.
At serving time, remove from freezer and place in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture and mix.

title: sandra's crescent roll-cream cheese pick-ups
directions: Spread 1 package crescent rolls in jelly roll pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and almond extract.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly and to edges.
Spread second package crescent rolls on top, stretching to edges.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Use your favorite recipe for meat loaf.
In place of tomato sauce, use spaghetti sauce.
Add Italian seasoning.
Prepare the rest as usual.
Just before it's done, add cheese on top, then finish baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Cook to boiling.
Lower heat; cook, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and marshmallows.
Cool.
Beat until slightly thickened; turn into a buttered pan about 11 x 7-inches.
Cut into squares when firm. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
Chop into chunks.
Add celery, onion, salad dressing, pickle relish and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chopped eggs.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar and vegetable oil.
Shake until sugar dissolves.
Drain beans, pour oil mixture over beans mix, cover and chill at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pork fried rice
directions: In 9-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add vegetables and cook over high heat, stirring frequently, until tender-crisp, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add rice, pork and soy sauce, stirring constantly, until rice has browned.
Add egg and stir until egg has set, about 1 minute.
Serves 2.
Contains 283 calories, 9 gm fat and 400 mg sodium.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix together and let stand 30 minutes or longer.
Squeeze out liquid with hands and pour off liquid.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Then add milk and margarine; cook over medium heat until thick.
Then add vanilla and drained pineapple. When cool, add container of Cool Whip for topping.

title: sweet-sour spareribs chinese style
directions: Rub spareribs with mustard and season with salt.
Heat cooker; add

title: cranberry orange jello
directions: In medium saucepan, melt cranberry sauce and add jello.
Mix. Bring to a boil.
Stir in oranges and pineapple.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups 7-Up and stir.
Mixture will foam up a bit.

title: moist cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Fold egg whites in last and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put
in blender and process until smooth.
It's so easy and inexpensive.
Just like the store bought.
Rich, thick and creamy. It
makes the same amount as the store bought and can be used in any recipe calling for sweetened condensed milk and costs a fraction of what it costs in the store.
Keeps several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: sausage cream cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll and place one can of crescent rolls in baking dish.
Fry sausage and drain.
While sausage is hot stir in cream cheese.
Spread mixture on top of rolls, and place second can of rolls on top.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until rolls are browned.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all
of
the ingredients and pour into a very large or 2 smaller pans. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for approximately 30 minutes to finish baking.

title: 5 layer blueberry tart
directions: Blend graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 300°.
Cool.
Cream margarine and add sugar.
Beat in eggs until light.
Spread over first layer.
Spread blueberry pie filling over second layer. Blend pineapple and whipped topping; spread over third layer. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight.

title: fired-up chili dip
directions: Combine chili and Ro-Tel in a medium saucepan.
Heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Pour into a shallow 1 1/2-quart bowl. arrange lettuce along outside edge to form a circle. Continue to arrange remaining ingredients in a circular pattern in order given or listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings. Enjoy.

title: karin's potato-nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add flour and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll into balls.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges lightly browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix butter, cake box mix, eggs, sugar and oil until smooth. Stir in sour cream; don't overmix.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread(aunt susie's specialty)
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters with scissors.
Shake biscuits in bag with white sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits in greased tube pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts between layers, if desired.
Melt brown sugar and margarine; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
To serve, just pinch off a piece and eat with fingers!
Serves 10.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake vigorously.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: scottish shortbread cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter and sugar.
Stir in the flour and mix thoroughly with hands.
Chill dough.
Roll out 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into shapes of your choice.
Flute edges, if desired, by pinching between fingers as for pie crust.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven between 20 to 25 minutes.

title: super-mix cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Place in oven to heat.
Beat egg in a bowl; stir in milk, corn and cheese.
Add cornbread mix; blend well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Allow to cool 5 to 10 minutes before slicing or handling.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown ground chuck and mix pepper, onions and celery.
Add chili powder and salt.
Add tomato juice, cabbage and beans. Simmer until cabbage is done.

title: ruth's hot fruit salad
directions: Put fruit in a large, ovenproof bowl.
Combine juice, brown sugar, flour, oleo and curry
and pour over fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut lard in with knife or fork.
Mix in water, vinegar and egg.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: bread sticks
directions: Let bread dough thaw enough to be able to tear into 20 strips. Roll strips in your hands and make each about 6 inches long. Place on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Let rise for 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix margarine and garlic powder.
Using a pastry brush, brush mixture on both sides of bread sticks.
You can also sprinkle garlic salt on the bread sticks.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: virginia's green enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add chiles,
soups, one cup milk (more if the sauce is too thick) and 1/2 cup of the grated cheese. Heat slowly until cheese is melted and
mixed in thoroughly.
Stir often to keep bottom from burning.
You can use a double boiler if you wish, but it is not necessary if you are careful.
When the sauce is ready, dip each tortilla in hot oil just until limp (3 to 5 seconds if the oil is hot enough).
Dip immediately into the sauce, put on a plate and fill with 1 to 2 tablespoons of grated cheese.
Roll and place in baking dish, seam side down. Continue until you have used all but about 1 cup of the sauce. Pour the remaining sauce over rolled tortillas and sprinkle with more grated cheese.
Place in oven, uncovered, on low heat (about 300°) until warmed throughout and cheese on top is melted (about 30 minutes).

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, sugar and all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat briskly with rotary or electric mixer until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from water and cool for a few minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until cold.
If too stiff, add 1 teaspoon of hot water beating briskly.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Season to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chunky sandwich spread
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Store and chill in a covered container at least one hour or until ready to use.

title: congealed grape salad
directions: Mix together the jello, water, pineapple and blueberry filling.
Pour in a dish and let set until firm, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Combine in a heavy pan and simmer for about an hour.
Shred meat with forks or mash with a potato masher.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Dump crushed pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Spread evenly (do not drain).
Dump blueberry pie filling and spread evenly over pineapple.
Dump yellow cake mixture (dry) over the blueberries.
Spread the chopped pecans over the cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in preheated oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash with onion until tender.
Drain; mix soup, cheese and 1/4 can water.
Combine all together.
Bake until hot.

title: punch
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups
water; melt over heat.
Cool and add lemon juice and 3 pints water.
Pour in ginger ale.
Add plenty of crushed ice.
Serves 40.

title: cranberry-cherry salad
directions: Heat
juice
and water mixture to boiling; set off heat and stir
in gelatin.
When completely dissolved, chill until slightly thickened.
Add
rest of ingredients and chill until firm.
Good with ham, chicken or turkey.

title: kevin's easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs and oil together.
Mix the baking soda and flour mixture.
Beat by hand.
Add the pineapple and nuts and mix lightly.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
This cake is very moist.

title: coney island sauce for hot dogs
directions: Fry meat and
onions
in
olive oil until brown.
Drain and put mixture through strainer.
Add dry ingredients.
Place in saucepan and
add
twice
as
much	water
as meat mixture. Simmer until most	of
mixture has been absorbed.	(Don't make too dry.) Serve over hot dog in roll.
Top with finely chopped Spanish onion.

title: pizza rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown beef with onion in melted butter in large skillet.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and cooked rice.
Layer rice mixture and meat sauce in a buttered casserole, ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Roll into balls or Easter shaped eggs.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and prick several times with a fork. Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Allow to cool to touch; cut potatoes in halves lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving about 1/4-inch thick shell; cut into inch wide strips and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Brush top of strips with butter; sprinkle with seasoning and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp.
Serve warm with sour cream.
Makes 3 dozen.
Reserve pulp for other uses.

title: scrumptious carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients, pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Pour batter in 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove and immediately spread Buttermilk Glaze over layers.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely, then spread Orange-Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cakes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in a heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Slowly add flour and simmer until well blended.
Very gradually add milk and simmer until sauce has thickened.
Add grated cheese and stir until sauce is smooth and cheese has melted.

title: hot punch
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan.
Heat, stirring often.

title: shortage squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Press into 6 x 8-inch pan. Dough is sticky!
Bake in 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut while warm.
Suggest candy size pieces.
Very rich!

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and margarine together until mixed well.
Add powdered sugar in small amounts and beat until smooth. Spread on cooled cake.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and Italian dressing.
Stir pasta and vegetables into dressing.
Chill.

title: broccoli crisp
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and place on bottom of lightly greased square baking dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter with all the cheese in top of double boiler.
Pour cheese over broccoli.
Melt the remaining butter and mix well with crushed crackers.
Spoon over broccoli and cheese.
Bake uncovered 375° until cheese bubbles and crumbs are lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix as directed on box and add milk and Cool Whip.
Mix and pour over bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Pour into a mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Will make two 12-inch pizzas or one 16-inch pizza.

title: mint surprise cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar well, adding sugars gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually and mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Insert 1 chocolate wafer in 1 tablespoon of chilled dough, making a ball.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix egg, sugar, flour, salt, vinegar and pineapple juice. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool. Fold in whipped cream Add fruit. Freeze.

title: southern hash browns
directions: Stir together oil, paprika, chili powder, salt and pepper; set aside. Lightly coat a baking sheet with nonstick vegetable spray and add potatoes in a single layer. Drizzle oil mixture over potatoes and bake at 400° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: amaretto coffee creamer
directions: Combine
all ingredients in a container with tight fitting lid.
Shake well to blend.
Store in an airtight container.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: In food processor blend bacon (uncooked), garlic and rosemary. Spread and pat paste on pork tenderloin.
Place on grill and cook 8 minutes on each side.

title: minto's nut rolls
directions: Heat milk until lukewarm.
Add yeast mix.
Mix rest of ingredients, then add to yeast mix.
Mix dough well.
Let dough rise until double in size.
Divide into 18 parts.
Roll out one at a time.
Fill with Nut Mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Cook together jello, sugar and juice from pineapple until thickened.
Cool.
Add the pineapple and cottage cheese.
Chill until set.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip and garnish with nuts if desired.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: In a small bowl, blend all ingredients well. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: sunday school rolls
directions: Mix on Saturday night.
Let rise until 8:00 a.m. Sunday.
Add a little more flour (1 to 2 cups).
Roll out.
Make crescents. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400° after church.

title: ginger cremes
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add brown sugar, shortening, molasses and egg.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Cook beef roast in oil in Dutch oven over medium to low heat until brown.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Add water and bouillon.
Add beef onion soup mix and onion.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cover and simmer on range top, about 3 1/2 hours.
Remove beef to platter.
Arrange potatoes and carrots around beef.

title: peach berry frozen salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and yogurt.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip, peaches, berries and almonds. Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover; freeze 8 to 24 hours or until firm.
To serve, thaw slightly and cut into squares.

title: nicole's reese's squares
directions: Mix butter and cracker crumbs together and add sugar and peanut butter.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate chips and refrigerate!

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all together. Put in pie shell. Bake in 300° oven 45 to 50 minutes.

title: crescent chicken rolls
directions: Chop
chicken
meat;
add
all	the
other ingredients. Separate rolls and place 1 or 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on dough and
roll
up, starting at wide end.	Place on ungreased cookie sheet and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed pears
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with cream cheese and add pecans.
Stuff pears with mixture and serve on lettuce.

title: corn dogs
directions: Dip in batter and deep fry.

title: hot bean compote
directions: Cook bacon crisp; set aside on paper towel.
To bacon drippings add next 5 ingredients; stir until smooth.
Add vinegar and beans, and cook over medium heat, stirring, for 30 minutes. Crumble bacon over top before serving.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into several long rolls.
Place in refrigerator. Slice and bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while cookies are still warm.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat on 2nd speed for 10 minutes.
Slice 3 or 4 apples, not too thin or thick.
Grease and flour pans.
Put in 1/3 batter (thick).
Top with apples, side by side.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine in 13x9x2 baking dish, croutons, cheese, and ham. Beat together the eggs and mustard. Add in the milk, salt, onion powder, and pepper; mix well. Pour over crouton mixture. Bake at 325° until eggs are set, about 55-60 minutes. Test by inserting knife in center (should come out clean).

title: classic potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 items; then add remaining items.
Cover and chill.
Yields 5 cups.

title: peanut butter and jelly thumbprint no-bake cookies
directions: In a large bowl, place popped corn; set aside.

In a medium saucepan, over medium-high heat, bring corn syrup to a boil and boil for 3 minutes; remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Working quickly, pour peanut mixture over popcorn, tossing gently to coat. Allow to cool 10 minutes.
Roll popcorn mixture into 18 (12-inch) balls.
Press thumb firmly into center of each ball. Fill each cookie center with 1/2 teaspoon jam. Store in airtight container.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixer bowl.
Add carrot, oil and eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer until combined.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted near the centers comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove cakes from pans.
Cool thoroughly on racks.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in hot water.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir well to mix.
Pour into a lightly greased mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Mix well and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard boil the eggs; let cool.
Remove the egg shells; cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks and mash them in a bowl. Add deviled ham, mayonnaise, mustard and relish and mix together. Place the egg yolks inside the egg whites and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix.
Pour into greased and floured pan(s).
Bake at 375° until done:
15 minutes for cupcakes, 25 minutes for 2 (9-inch) layers or 35 minutes for tube or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients together; mix well.
Do not use mixer.

title: gold
directions: Cut potatoes and boil until tender; mash.
Cut carrots and boil until very tender.
Mash.
Combine potatoes, carrots and butter; mash together until well mixed.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cream of wheat dumplings
directions: Beat all together with hand mixer.
Drop from teaspoon into boiling chicken broth.
Boil for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and chocolate morsels in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until chocolate melts and mixture boils.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve hot over ice cream.
Yields 1 cup.

title: diabetic corn bread
directions: Preheat a greased small iron skillet in a 500° oven.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a hot skillet.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Thaw squash.
Beat eggs and milk. Add flour and rest of ingredients.
Beat well. Add squash and beat again.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.
This can be made the day before,
refrigerated and warmed before serving.
It is delicious.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and oleo on medium heat for 5 minutes after it starts to boil.
Take off stove and add Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until completely mixed, then pour into buttered 11 x 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool completely before slicing.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to box directions.
Mix cottage cheese, pepper and salt.
Brown together meats.
Drain.
Add meats to Ragu sauce.
Cook slowly until flavors blend.

title: slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over cabbage. Make day before using.
Will keep several days.

title: mushroom chicken(pheasant)
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Brown in 1 tablespoon oil; drain, then add ingredients.
Let simmer on medium low for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Serve over rice or potatoes and enjoy.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and next 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add bananas, egg, oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets about 2 inches apart.
Top each with a nut.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in 3 cups water for approximately 35 minutes.
Drain and allow to cool.
Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Combine green onions, red bell pepper and celery with potatoes.
Chill for 2 hours.
Mix mayonnaise, yogurt, mustard, horseradish and white pepper and pour over chilled potato mixture. Toss gently.
Sprinkle paprika and shredded carrots on top. Makes 6 servings.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In large bowl, coat meat with 1/4 cup flour.
In skillet or Dutch oven over heat, brown meat and onions in oil.
Stir in paprika, salt, marjoram, pepper, green pepper, garlic, water and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours, until meat is tender.
Mix 3 tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup water; stir into mixture.
Heat until it boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve over noodles or potatoes.

title: pumpkin bread pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 9x11 baking dish (in water) 350 degrees for 50 minutes; or 420 degrees for 10 minutes. This can be made with artificial sweetener for diabetes.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Choose seedless cucumbers, if available.
Cut cucumbers paper thin; sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Dry on paper towel and place in a dish.
Mix the vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar; pour over cucumbers.
Sprinkle with chopped dill.
Store in covered jar or dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve as needed. Makes 2 cups.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in steamer with lid for 20 minutes.
Drain well. Combine sugar, honey, salt and oil.
Place carrots in baking dish; coat with glaze.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chex party mix
directions: In small bowl, add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce to melted butter; mix well.
Pour Chex cereals, nuts and pretzels into large Glad-lock zipper bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside zipper bag.
Seal top and shake until pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents of bag into large microwave safe bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes. Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: easy rice dressing
directions: If you don't have time for the long version, this is a quick and easy substitute.
Combine all the ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Make sure lid fits tightly on casserole dish.

title: soy milk
directions: Blend until smooth and chill.
Shake before serving.

title: real mexican salsa dip
directions: Blend all the ingredients in blender until desired consistency is reached.
Use your favorite Tostitos chips to dip with.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Rinse peppers.
Slice tops off.
Pull out seeds.
For stuffing, combine bread crumbs and milk.
Let sit for 10 minutes. Peel and chop onions.
In a bowl, combine ground meat, onions, bread crumb mixture and egg yolk.
Mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers.
Place peppers in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Baste with liquid from pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 additional minutes.

title: low calorie slaw dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar with a tight-fitting lid.
Shake well.

title: missouri earthquake cake
directions: Baste bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with pecans, then coconut.
Mix the cake mix according to directions on box; pour over coconut mixture.
Mix the cream cheese, melted margarine, vanilla and confectioners sugar to pouring consistency; pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brigadeiro
directions: Put a little bit of margarine in a pan over medium heat.
When margarine is melted, pour the condensed milk in the pan and stir constantly for 5 minutes.
Add honey and as much cocoa powder as you like.
Keep stirring; don't stop stirring!
When it boils and you can see the bottom of the pan, take it off the heat.
When cool, make very little balls and roll them in chocolate sprinkles or coconut.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and milk in heavy 1-quart saucepan until well blended. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and sugar is dissolved. Cook until candy reaches soft ball stage. Stir often and mix well. Add nuts and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and quickly break apart.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: If desired, add slice of tomato, lettuce, slice of ham, etc.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add peaches and juice evenly. Mix other ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: granola
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large roasting pan.
In a small saucepan, combine oil, honey and vanilla.
Bring to a boil. Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes, stirring several times.
Cool and store in a tightly covered container in a cool, dry area.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: jalapeno hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Using a fork, drop heaping portions of mixture into hot, deep fat at 350°.
Fry each hush puppy approximately 3 minutes, or until golden brown.
Turn once during cooking.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Yields approximately 30 hush puppies.

title: banana delight
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, margarine, 2 tablespoons sugar and nuts.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Cool.
Beat the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust.
Slice bananas on top of cream cheese layer.
Beat the pudding mix and 3 cups milk until thick; spread over layer of bananas.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.
Top may be sprinkled with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: royal italian style spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion, green peppers and parsley.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually add chicken stock and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken and lemon juice.
Stir and heat to serving temperature.

title: blitz torte
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into 2 layer cake pans, greased.

title: cold pink borscht or beet and cucumber soup
directions: Cook beets (whole), then skin them.
Peel and seed cucumbers and cut into several chunks.
Put all ingredients, except sour cream, in food processor and run until smooth.
Whisk in sour cream and taste for seasoning.
May add garnish of chopped chives (or 1 of the beets chopped instead of processed).
Serve cold.

title: garlicky cranberry chutney
directions: Cut ginger into paper thin slices; stack them together and cut into really thin slivers. Combine ginger, garlic, vinegar, sugar and cayenne in a small pot. Bring to a simmer; simmer on medium heat about 15 minutes or until there are about 4 tablespoons of liquid left.

Add can of cranberry sauce, salt and pepper. Mix and bring to a simmer. Lumps are okay. Simmer on a gentle heat for about 10 minutes. Cool, store and refrigerate. (It will keep for several days, if you don't finish it all after the first taste.)

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle dry soup in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add 1 cup rice. Mix together 2 cans soup with 2 cans water.
Pour over soup and rice without mixing.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325° uncovered.

title: omelette casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole with 6 slices buttered bread. On top of each, place 1 slice of American cheese.
Sprinkle with ham, pepper and onion.
Place 6 remaining slices of buttered bread on top and sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Mix 12 eggs and milk in blender.
Pour over entire casserole and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then down to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, water, yeast and shortening.
Beat. Add flour, 4 cups at a time.
Let rise in refrigerator overnight. Roll out dough and cut into rolls.
Let rise 30 minutes in a warm place or up to 3 hours in a cool place.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: pepper steak(20 minutes)
directions: Trim fat from beef and cut into strips.
Heat oil in large skillet. Cook beef until brown.
Stir in water, onions, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add peppers during last 5 minutes.
Cook rice as package directs.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir into beef mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.

title: cavatini
directions: Place about 3 cups uncooked rotini noodles in boiling water. Cook until tender, but not totally done.
Brown sausage and drain. Place sausage over noodles in large casserole dish.
Place onion, pepper and sliced mushrooms over sausage.
Place sliced pepperoni over these ingredients.
Pour spaghetti sauce over pepperoni and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate for several hours. Cook over grill (6 to 8 minutes), turning and basting.
Serves 4 people.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together and spread in greased plate.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: baked butternut squash
directions: Put squash in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with spices combined with brown sugar.
Add lemon juice to butter and drizzle over squash.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: broccoli whiz
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in small casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate marble cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs and melted butter.
Lightly grease bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Press mixture onto bottom of pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.

title: new potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes and boil until soft in the middle.
Drain. Mix soup, sour cream, butter and onion.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: white chocolate cereal snacks
directions: Melt white chocolate.
Mix cereals, nuts and pretzels well, then add warm chocolate.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Let set for 1 hour.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Combine all except bread crumbs and butter.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of crab mixture.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes and crumbs are golden. Serves 6.
Fresh shrimp and crab may be used instead of canned.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in an oiled sheet cake pan in 375° to 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: carrot cake(the best ever)
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Combine with first mixture. Add carrots and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add egg, lemon rind, vanilla and cherry juice.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then raisins and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon into crushed cereal, roll into balls, coat well and top with maraschino cherries.
Bake on greased cookie sheets in hot oven (400°) about 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
Recipe makes two dozen.

title: beef 'n' barley stew
directions: In shallow, 1-quart microwavable casserole, combine 1 cup water, the tomato paste and broth mix, stirring to dissolve tomato paste.
Add barley and stir to combine.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) for 10 minutes, stirring every 2 1/2 minutes.

title: hearty lunch salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Top salad with potatoes just before serving.

title: two bowl cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk together; set aside.
Beat shortening, soda and water together, then add first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Slice off one side of eggplant.
Remove pulp to within 1/2-inch of skin.
Boil 1/2 cup water with 1/2 teaspoon salt; add eggplant pulp and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Cook onion in butter until tender, not brown.
Add eggplant pulp, parsley, soup, sauce and all cracker crumbs, except 2 tablespoons.
Fill eggplant shell with mixture and place in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Pour 1 cup of water into dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
